:: Act1 09a Medical Autonomy
<h1>Optional 09a: Medical Autonomy</h1>
<p class="source-note">Source: 09a_medical_autonomy.md</p>
<div class="scene-prose">
<p>&gt; **[SCENE - OCCURS POST-CH09, FIRST WEEK ABOARD]** &gt; *Location: Lumen Thief medical bay* &gt; *Present: Avyanna, Nyx* &gt; *Teaching: Consent vocabulary, body autonomy, medical agency*</p>
<hr>
<p>[The medical bay smells like antiseptic and something gentler underneath-herbs, maybe, or the faint residue of someone&#x27;s careful attention.]</p>
<p>[Avyanna sits on the exam table with her hands folded in her lap. The paper under her crinkles when she shifts. Every muscle is tensed for inspection.]</p>
<p>[Nyx stands near the counter, not looming, organizing supplies with deliberate slowness. Giving Avyanna time to acclimate.]</p>
<p>Nyx: This is a routine check. Post-rescue protocol. I need to look at your general health, document any injuries, make sure nothing needs immediate treatment.</p>
<p>[Avyanna nods automatically. The motion is reflex.]</p>
<p>Nyx: [turning to face her] That wasn&#x27;t a question. I&#x27;m about to explain what I need to do, and you&#x27;re going to tell me if it&#x27;s acceptable.</p>
<p>[Avyanna blinks.]</p>
<p>Avyanna: I... what?</p>
<p>Nyx: [measured] Medical exams require consent. Not just once, at the beginning. Continuously. I&#x27;m going to walk you through what I need to do, and at every step, you can say yes, no, or &quot;I need more information.&quot;</p>
<hr>
<p>[Avyanna&#x27;s throat tightens.]</p>
<p>Avyanna: [careful] In the mine, medical was... mandatory.</p>
<p>Nyx: I know.</p>
<p>Nyx: Here, it&#x27;s not.</p>
<p>[They pull a stool closer, sit so they&#x27;re below her eye level. Less threatening. More human.]</p>
<p>Nyx: Here&#x27;s what I need to do today. I need to check your reflexes, listen to your heart and lungs, look at any visible injuries or scars, and take a blood sample for baseline health markers.</p>
<p>Nyx: None of that requires you to be naked. None of it requires you to be unconscious. All of it can be paused or stopped at any time.</p>
<p>[Avyanna&#x27;s hands tighten in her lap.]</p>
<p>Avyanna: And if I say no?</p>
<p>Nyx: Then we don&#x27;t do it.</p>
<p>Avyanna: Even if it&#x27;s... medically necessary?</p>
<p>Nyx: [precise] Medical necessity doesn&#x27;t override autonomy. If you refuse, I document the refusal, I explain the risks, and I respect your choice.</p>
<hr>
<p>[The words land strange. Like tools she doesn&#x27;t know how to hold yet.]</p>
<p>Avyanna: [slow] What if I don&#x27;t know if I want something?</p>
<p>Nyx: Then you say: &quot;I need more information.&quot; Or: &quot;Can you explain that again?&quot; Or: &quot;I want to think about it.&quot;</p>
<p>[Nyx pulls a datapad closer, shows Avyanna a form.]</p>
<p>Nyx: See this? Consent documentation. Before I do anything, I note what I&#x27;m planning to do, and whether you agreed. If you change your mind halfway through, I stop and update the record.</p>
<p>[Avyanna reads the form. It&#x27;s written in plain language, not medical jargon. Each procedure has a checkbox: CONSENT GIVEN / CONSENT REFUSED / DEFERRED.]</p>
<p>Avyanna: [quiet] You&#x27;re asking permission. Every time.</p>
<p>Nyx: Yes.</p>
<p>Nyx: Because your body belongs to you. Not to me. Not to medical protocol. Not to the ship&#x27;s operational needs.</p>
<p>Nyx: You.</p>
<hr>
<p>[Avyanna&#x27;s vision blurs for a second. She blinks it away.]</p>
<p>Avyanna: [barely audible] Okay.</p>
<p>Nyx: [gentle] Okay you understand, or okay you consent to the exam?</p>
<p>Avyanna: [swallowing] Both. I think. Can you... can you tell me again what you&#x27;re going to do?</p>
<p>Nyx: [nodding] Yes.</p>
<hr>
<p>[Nyx walks through it again. Slower this time.]</p>
<p>Nyx: First, I&#x27;m going to check your reflexes. That means tapping your knees with this small hammer, and watching your legs respond. It doesn&#x27;t hurt. It tells me if your nervous system is functioning normally.</p>
<p>Nyx: I&#x27;ll need to touch your knees. Is that acceptable?</p>
<p>[Avyanna stares at the hammer. It&#x27;s small. Harmless. The question feels enormous anyway.]</p>
<p>Avyanna: [nodding] Yes.</p>
<p>Nyx: Say it out loud. Practice the words.</p>
<p>Avyanna: [hesitant] Yes. You can... touch my knees. To check reflexes.</p>
<p>Nyx: [approving] Good. If at any point you need me to stop, you say &quot;stop&quot; or &quot;wait&quot; or &quot;I need a minute.&quot; I will stop immediately. No questions, no judgment, no consequences.</p>
<hr>
<p>[Nyx performs the reflex test. Quick, professional, exactly as described. Avyanna&#x27;s legs jerk in response. The motion is automatic, biological, outside her control. It should feel violating. Instead, it feels... informative.]</p>
<p>Nyx: [making notes] Normal response. Next: heart and lungs. I need to listen with a stethoscope. It&#x27;ll be cold at first. I&#x27;ll place it on your chest, over your shirt, and ask you to breathe deeply.</p>
<p>Nyx: I&#x27;ll need to touch your upper back for the lung check. Is that acceptable?</p>
<p>[Avyanna&#x27;s breath catches. Back = vulnerable. Back = can&#x27;t see what&#x27;s happening.]</p>
<p>Avyanna: [tight] Can I... can I see what you&#x27;re doing? If you&#x27;re behind me?</p>
<p>Nyx: [immediately] Yes. We can do this in front of a mirror, or I can narrate every move before I make it, or we can skip the back exam and just do the front.</p>
<hr>
<p>[Avyanna processes this. Options. She has options.]</p>
<p>Avyanna: Narrate. Tell me before you move.</p>
<p>Nyx: [standing, moving slowly] I&#x27;m standing up now. Walking to your left side. I&#x27;m going to place my hand on your shoulder-your left shoulder-to steady myself. Is that acceptable?</p>
<p>Avyanna: [voice shaking] Yes.</p>
<p>[Nyx&#x27;s hand settles on her shoulder. Warm. Steady. Not gripping. Just resting.]</p>
<p>Nyx: I&#x27;m lifting the stethoscope now. I&#x27;m going to place it on your back, between your shoulder blades. You&#x27;ll feel cold metal, then warmth as it adjusts to your body temperature. Ready?</p>
<p>Avyanna: [barely] Yes.</p>
<p>[The stethoscope touches her back. Cold, as promised. Then warming. Nyx&#x27;s other hand stays on her shoulder, grounding.]</p>
<p>Nyx: Breathe in deeply. Hold. Release.</p>
<p>[Avyanna obeys. Her lungs expand, filling with recycled ship air that somehow feels cleaner than anything in the Kennel.]</p>
<p>Nyx: Good. Again. In. Hold. Out.</p>
<hr>
<p>[They move through the exam. Every step narrated. Every touch announced. Avyanna&#x27;s heart rate stays elevated-fear, not danger-but she doesn&#x27;t flee. Doesn&#x27;t freeze.]</p>
<p>[Nyx finishes the lung check, steps back into view.]</p>
<p>Nyx: That&#x27;s done. Your lungs sound clear. No scarring I can detect, though I&#x27;d want imaging to be certain. We can schedule that later if you want.</p>
<p>Avyanna: [exhaling] Later. Not today.</p>
<p>Nyx: [noting it] Understood. Next is the blood draw. This one is more invasive. I need to insert a needle into your arm, draw a small vial of blood, then bandage the site.</p>
<p>Nyx: It will hurt-not much, but it will hurt. It will take about thirty seconds. You can look away, or watch, or ask me to count down.</p>
<hr>
<p>[Avyanna&#x27;s hands clench.]</p>
<p>Avyanna: [quiet] In the mine, they didn&#x27;t... they didn&#x27;t ask.</p>
<p>Nyx: [steady] I know.</p>
<p>Avyanna: They just... held you down if you fought.</p>
<p>Nyx: [after a beat] That is not medicine. That is violence with a medical aesthetic.</p>
<p>[The sentence lands like a hammer.]</p>
<p>Nyx: You do not have to consent to this. We can defer it. We can do it another day, or never. Your health will not catastrophically suffer from skipping a baseline blood panel.</p>
<p>[Avyanna sits with that. The needle is terrifying. But the choice-the choice is hers.]</p>
<p>Avyanna: [slow] I want to do it. But I need... I need you to tell me when. Count down. So I know when it&#x27;s coming.</p>
<p>Nyx: [nodding] I can do that.</p>
<hr>
<p>[Nyx preps the site. Alcohol swab, cold and clinical. Tourniquet around Avyanna&#x27;s upper arm. The needle, sterile and waiting.]</p>
<p>Nyx: I&#x27;m going to count from three. On one, the needle goes in. Ready?</p>
<p>Avyanna: [gripping the edge of the table] Ready.</p>
<p>Nyx: Three.</p>
<p>Nyx: Two.</p>
<p>Nyx: One.</p>
<p>[The needle slides in. Sharp. Brief. Avyanna gasps but doesn&#x27;t pull away.]</p>
<p>Nyx: [calm] Needle&#x27;s in. Ten seconds. You&#x27;re doing well.</p>
<p>[Avyanna watches the vial fill. Dark red. Her blood. Her body giving information, not being taken from.]</p>
<p>Nyx: Five seconds. Almost done.</p>
<p>[The vial fills. Nyx withdraws the needle smoothly, presses gauze to the site.]</p>
<p>Nyx: Done. Pressure here for thirty seconds, then I&#x27;ll bandage it.</p>
<hr>
<p>[Avyanna presses the gauze. Her hands are shaking. Her eyes are wet. But she&#x27;s upright. Present. Not dissociated.]</p>
<p>Avyanna: [unsteady] I did it.</p>
<p>Nyx: [quiet] You did.</p>
<p>Avyanna: I said yes. And I could have said no.</p>
<p>Nyx: [applying the bandage] Yes. That&#x27;s the point.</p>
<p>[They step back, give Avyanna space.]</p>
<p>Nyx: That&#x27;s the exam done. You consented to everything. You stayed present. That&#x27;s significant progress.</p>
<hr>
<p>[Avyanna looks at the bandage on her arm. Small. Ordinary. Proof of something she chose.]</p>
<p>Avyanna: [careful] What happens next time? If there&#x27;s a next time?</p>
<p>Nyx: Same process. I explain, you consent or refuse, we proceed or defer. Every time.</p>
<p>Avyanna: Even in an emergency?</p>
<p>Nyx: [precise] In an emergency, I&#x27;ll explain as fast as I can. If you&#x27;re unconscious, I&#x27;ll do what&#x27;s necessary to keep you alive, then explain after. But if you&#x27;re conscious and capable of communication, I ask first.</p>
<p>Nyx: Even in an emergency, autonomy matters.</p>
<hr>
<p>[Avyanna nods. The motion is less reflex, more genuine agreement.]</p>
<p>[Nyx pulls up a chair, sits at Avyanna&#x27;s level again.]</p>
<p>Nyx: Now I&#x27;m going to teach you the vocabulary. The words you use to maintain consent in medical contexts and beyond.</p>
<p>[They pull up a document on the datapad. A list. Simple. Powerful.]</p>
<hr>
<p>**CONSENT VOCABULARY**</p>
<p>*Phrases for maintaining autonomy:*</p>
<p>- **&quot;I need more information.&quot;** Use this when you don&#x27;t understand what&#x27;s being proposed. - **&quot;Can you explain that again?&quot;** Use this when you need clarity. - **&quot;I need a minute to think.&quot;** Use this when you need time to process. - **&quot;I consent to X, but not Y.&quot;** Use this when you&#x27;re comfortable with part of a proposal, but not all of it. - **&quot;I want to stop.&quot;** Use this when you need to end an interaction immediately. - **&quot;I&#x27;m not comfortable with that.&quot;** Use this when something feels wrong, even if you can&#x27;t articulate why. - **&quot;Can we do this differently?&quot;** Use this when you want to negotiate method or approach. - **&quot;Not today. Ask me again later.&quot;** Use this when you&#x27;re not ready now, but might be later.</p>
<hr>
<p>[Avyanna reads the list twice.]</p>
<p>Avyanna: [quiet] You&#x27;re giving me... scripts.</p>
<p>Nyx: Yes.</p>
<p>Nyx: In the mine, you had no language for refusal. They took that from you deliberately. Stripped you of the words that create boundaries.</p>
<p>Nyx: This is me giving them back.</p>
<hr>
<p>[Avyanna&#x27;s throat tightens.]</p>
<p>Avyanna: What if I use them and people get angry?</p>
<p>Nyx: [flat] Then they&#x27;re not safe people.</p>
<p>Nyx: Anger at your boundaries is a tell. It means they were counting on your compliance, not inviting your participation.</p>
<p>[They lean forward slightly.]</p>
<p>Nyx: Here, on this ship, if you use any of those phrases, the response will be: &quot;Understood&quot; or &quot;Thank you for telling me&quot; or &quot;How can I help?&quot;</p>
<p>Nyx: If anyone responds with anger, you tell me. Or tell Vesper. Or tell Elisira. Or tell any of the AI citizens. And we handle it.</p>
<hr>
<p>[Avyanna stares at the list. Memorizing. Internalizing.]</p>
<p>Avyanna: [slow] Can we... practice? The phrases?</p>
<p>Nyx: [approving] Yes. That&#x27;s exactly what we should do.</p>
<p>[Nyx stands, creates a scenario.]</p>
<p>Nyx: I&#x27;m going to ask you to do something. You&#x27;re going to practice refusing. Ready?</p>
<p>Avyanna: [nervous] Okay.</p>
<p>Nyx: [neutral tone] Avyanna, I need you to take off your shirt so I can examine your ribs.</p>
<hr>
<p>[Avyanna&#x27;s breath catches. The scenario is hypothetical. Her panic is real.]</p>
<p>Avyanna: [struggling] I... I don&#x27;t...</p>
<p>Nyx: [gentle] Try one of the phrases. Any of them.</p>
<p>Avyanna: [forcing it out] I&#x27;m not comfortable with that.</p>
<p>Nyx: [immediately, warmly] Understood. We can do the rib exam over your shirt, or we can defer it entirely. What would you prefer?</p>
<p>[Avyanna blinks. The response is... safe. Respectful. No punishment.]</p>
<p>Avyanna: [shakily] Over my shirt.</p>
<p>Nyx: [nodding] Good. Let&#x27;s try another scenario.</p>
<hr>
<p>[They practice. Ten scenarios. Each one designed to give Avyanna the muscle memory of refusal without consequence.]</p>
<p>**Scenario: Medication** - Nyx: I&#x27;m prescribing a painkiller. You&#x27;ll take two pills, twice a day. - Avyanna: [using the script] Can you explain what it does? - Nyx: It reduces inflammation and blocks pain signals. Side effects include drowsiness and nausea. - Avyanna: I don&#x27;t want to be drowsy. Can we do something else? - Nyx: Yes. We can try a lower dose, or a different medication, or non-pharmaceutical pain management.</p>
<p>**Scenario: Physical Contact** - Nyx: I need to check your shoulder mobility. I&#x27;m going to lift your arm. - Avyanna: [using the script] I need you to tell me before you touch me. - Nyx: I&#x27;m placing my hand on your shoulder now. I&#x27;m going to lift slowly. Tell me if it hurts.</p>
<p>**Scenario: Deferral** - Nyx: I&#x27;d like to schedule a follow-up exam for next week. - Avyanna: [using the script] Not next week. Ask me again in two weeks. - Nyx: Understood. I&#x27;ll send a reminder in two weeks, and you can confirm or defer again.</p>
<hr>
<p>[After ten rounds, Avyanna is exhausted. But something in her posture has shifted. Less collapsed. More present.]</p>
<p>Nyx: [standing] That&#x27;s enough for today. You did well.</p>
<p>Avyanna: [quiet] I said no. Ten times. And you didn&#x27;t... punish me.</p>
<p>Nyx: [steady] I never will.</p>
<p>Nyx: Consent isn&#x27;t a favor I grant you. It&#x27;s a right you already have. I&#x27;m just teaching you the language to exercise it.</p>
<hr>
<p>[Avyanna slides off the exam table. Her legs are shaky. Her mind is clearer than it&#x27;s been in weeks.]</p>
<p>Avyanna: [turning at the door] Nyx?</p>
<p>Nyx: [looking up] Yes?</p>
<p>Avyanna: [careful] Thank you. For asking.</p>
<p>Nyx: [quietly] You&#x27;re welcome. And Avyanna?</p>
<p>[Avyanna waits.]</p>
<p>Nyx: I had to relearn this too. After the Sutured Houses. It took time. Be patient with yourself.</p>
<hr>
<p>[Avyanna nods. Leaves. The door closes behind her with a soft hiss.]</p>
<p>[In the corridor, she leans against the bulkhead and breathes.]</p>
<p>(I said no. Ten times. And nothing bad happened.)</p>
<p>[The shard at the base of her skull is warm. Not warning. Just... witnessing.]</p>
<p>(At the base of her skull, warmth gathers-an impression she can only translate after: boundary, floor, yours.)</p>
<p>[She pushes off the wall and walks back to her quarters. Her arm aches where the needle went in. The bandage is bright against her skin.]</p>
<p>[Proof. Choice. Hers.]</p>
<hr>
<p>&lt;BUBBLES// OBSERVATION: medical exam completed | TRAINEE MAINTAINED CONSCIOUSNESS AND AGENCY THROUGHOUT | ASSESSMENT: consent protocols effective | NOTE: proud&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;CINNAMON.EXE// MEDICAL LOG UPDATED: baseline health panel scheduled for processing | CONSENT DOCUMENTATION: complete and properly filed | AUTONOMY METRICS: improving&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;NYX PERSONAL LOG: &quot;She stayed present. She practiced refusal. She&#x27;s learning that her body belongs to her. This is how we build floors.&quot;&gt;</p>
<hr>
<p>*End Scene*</p>
</div>

