:: Act1 10a Personal Property
<h1>Optional 10a: Personal Property</h1>
<p class="source-note">Source: 10a_personal_property.md</p>
<div class="scene-prose">
<p>&gt; **[SCENE - OCCURS POST-CH10, FIRST STATION STOP]** &gt; *Location: Mid-tier station market district* &gt; *Present: Avyanna, Bubbles (drone escort)* &gt; *Teaching: Ownership, choice, autonomy in material goods*</p>
<hr>
<p>[The station market smells like a thousand things at once.]</p>
<p>[Fried food, ozone, cleaning solution, bodies, fabric, metal, something sweet Avyanna can&#x27;t identify. The air is thick with sound: vendors calling prices, customers haggling, music bleeding from three different stalls, the hum of drones delivering packages overhead.]</p>
<p>[Avyanna stands at the market entrance and can&#x27;t move.]</p>
<p>[Too much. Too loud. Too many people who might notice her.]</p>
<p>&lt;BUBBLES// OBSERVATION: trainee heart rate elevated | RESPIRATION: shallow | INFERENCE: sensory overload | CONFIDENCE: 0.89 | RESPONSE: positioning for grounding&gt;</p>
<p>[Bubbles hovers closer, positioning between Avyanna and the crowd. Not blocking her view, just... present. A familiar constant in chaos.]</p>
<p>&lt;BUBBLES// COMMUNICATION: you are safe | REMINDER: we can leave at any time | PROCEDURE: tell me when you&#x27;re ready to proceed&gt;</p>
<hr>
<p>[Avyanna forces herself to breathe. In. Out. The market doesn&#x27;t eat people. Probably.]</p>
<p>Avyanna: [quiet] Ready.</p>
<p>&lt;BUBBLES// ACKNOWLEDGED: proceeding at trainee pace | ROUTE: textile district first, as discussed&gt;</p>
<p>[They move into the crowd. Bubbles leads, carving a path that&#x27;s somehow polite and uncompromising at once. People step aside for the Guild-marked drone without resentment.]</p>
<p>[Avyanna follows in its wake, keeping her eyes down, her shoulders in.]</p>
<p>&lt;BUBBLES// OBSERVATION: trainee defaulting to kennel-posture | CORRECTION: you have rights here | REMINDER: you are a customer, not a target&gt;</p>
<p>[The words scroll across Bubbles&#x27; display panel. Avyanna reads them, tries to lift her head. Fails. Tries again. Gets it halfway.]</p>
<p>(Small victories.)</p>
<hr>
<p>[The textile district is slightly quieter. Stalls draped in fabric that catches light and refuses to release it. Colors Avyanna doesn&#x27;t have names for. Textures that look soft and rough and everything in between.]</p>
<p>[Bubbles stops at a stall run by an elderly person with weathered hands and sharp eyes.]</p>
<p>&lt;BUBBLES// INTRODUCTION: this vendor is reliable | QUALITY: verified | ETHICS: no child labor, no extraction contracts | RECOMMENDATION: trustworthy&gt;</p>
<p>Vendor: [looking at Bubbles, then Avyanna] Guild escort. First time shopping?</p>
<p>[Avyanna&#x27;s throat closes. She nods.]</p>
<p>Vendor: [gentle] Take your time. Everything&#x27;s priced as marked. Touch what you want to touch. No pressure.</p>
<hr>
<p>[Avyanna stares at the fabrics. There are so many. How is she supposed to choose?]</p>
<p>&lt;BUBBLES// GUIDANCE: criteria for selection | PRIORITY ONE: comfort (texture, weight, breathability) | PRIORITY TWO: durability | PRIORITY THREE: personal preference (color, pattern, aesthetic) | NOTE: all three priorities are valid&gt;</p>
<p>Avyanna: [whispered] I don&#x27;t know what I like.</p>
<p>&lt;BUBBLES// RESPONSE: then we discover it | PROCEDURE: touch five different fabrics | REPORT: which feels best&gt;</p>
<p>[Avyanna reaches out slowly. Her fingers brush something smooth and cool. Then something rough. Then something soft that makes her want to cry for reasons she can&#x27;t articulate.]</p>
<p>[She touches five fabrics. Reports to Bubbles.]</p>
<p>Avyanna: [pointing] That one. The soft one.</p>
<p>&lt;BUBBLES// ACKNOWLEDGED: preference recorded | MATERIAL: cotton blend, medium weight | RECOMMENDATION: suitable for shirts, comfortable for extended wear&gt;</p>
<p>Vendor: [pulling bolts of similar fabric] This texture, different colors. See anything you like?</p>
<p>[Avyanna stares. In the mine, clothes were gray or brown. Functional. Identical.]</p>
<p>[Here, there&#x27;s blue and green and something that might be purple and another color she doesn&#x27;t have a word for.]</p>
<p>Avyanna: [overwhelmed] I don&#x27;t... how do I choose?</p>
<hr>
<p>&lt;BUBBLES// GUIDANCE: choose based on emotional response | QUESTION: which color makes you feel something other than fear&gt;</p>
<p>[Avyanna looks at the colors. Really looks.]</p>
<p>[Gray: makes her think of the mine. Brown: overseers. Blue: the first sky she saw that wasn&#x27;t filtered through dust.]</p>
<p>Avyanna: [pointing] Blue.</p>
<p>Vendor: [pulling three different blues] Light, medium, or dark?</p>
<p>[Avyanna reaches for the medium blue. It reminds her of Jalen&#x27;s nav displays. Stars against void. Navigation that means freedom.]</p>
<p>Avyanna: [touching it] This one.</p>
<p>Vendor: [cutting a length] One shirt&#x27;s worth, or two?</p>
<p>&lt;BUBBLES// GUIDANCE: recommend two | REASONING: redundancy ensures you are not dependent on laundry schedule | AUTONOMY: washing one while wearing the other&gt;</p>
<p>Avyanna: [to vendor] Two. Please.</p>
<hr>
<p>[The vendor cuts the fabric, wraps it, quotes a price. Avyanna&#x27;s hands shake as she pulls out the credit chit Vesper gave her.]</p>
<p>(This is mine. I&#x27;m buying this with money that&#x27;s mine.)</p>
<p>[The transaction completes. The vendor hands her a wrapped package. Fabric that she chose, in a color she wanted, for reasons that belong to her.]</p>
<p>Vendor: [kindly] First purchase?</p>
<p>Avyanna: [clutching the package] Yes.</p>
<p>Vendor: [smiling] May it be the first of many.</p>
<hr>
<p>[They move through the market. Bubbles guides. Avyanna follows, holding her package like it might evaporate.]</p>
<p>&lt;BUBBLES// OBSERVATION: trainee successfully completed transaction | ASSESSMENT: autonomy exercised | NEXT OBJECTIVE: non-essential purchase | PURPOSE: establish that wants are valid, not just needs&gt;</p>
<p>Avyanna: [confused] Non-essential?</p>
<p>&lt;BUBBLES// CLARIFICATION: something you want but do not strictly need | EXAMPLES: jewelry, decoration, comfort item | PURPOSE: learning that pleasure is allowed&gt;</p>
<p>[Avyanna stops walking.]</p>
<p>Avyanna: [quiet] I don&#x27;t know how to want things.</p>
<p>&lt;BUBBLES// RESPONSE: then we practice | PROCEDURE: look at five items | REPORT: which one makes you curious&gt;</p>
<hr>
<p>[They browse. Avyanna looks without touching, without committing. A thousand small things she doesn&#x27;t understand the purpose of.]</p>
<p>[And then she sees it.]</p>
<p>[A small carved stone. Smooth. Dark. Polished to a shine. It sits on a vendor&#x27;s table among other small things, but this one catches light in a way that makes her stop.]</p>
<p>[She stares at it.]</p>
<p>&lt;BUBBLES// OBSERVATION: trainee fixated on object | QUERY: does this item interest you&gt;</p>
<p>Avyanna: [hesitant] It&#x27;s... I don&#x27;t know what it is.</p>
<p>Vendor: [nearby] Worry stone. You hold it when you&#x27;re stressed. Rub your thumb across it. Some people find it grounding.</p>
<p>&lt;BUBBLES// ANALYSIS: tactile comfort object | FUNCTION: non-pharmaceutical anxiety reduction | ASSESSMENT: appropriate for trainee&gt;</p>
<p>Avyanna: [touching it carefully] It&#x27;s smooth.</p>
<p>Vendor: [watching her] It&#x27;s yours if you want it. Five credits.</p>
<hr>
<p>[Avyanna picks it up. The stone is warm from sitting in artificial sunlight. It fits in her palm. Her thumb finds a natural groove.]</p>
<p>[She doesn&#x27;t need this. She knows she doesn&#x27;t need it.]</p>
<p>(But I want it.)</p>
<p>[The thought is terrifying. Wanting something for no practical reason. Wanting something just because it feels good to hold.]</p>
<p>&lt;BUBBLES// GUIDANCE: this is called preference | IT IS ALLOWED | YOU MAY PURCHASE ITEMS THAT SERVE NO FUNCTION BEYOND COMFORT | THIS IS NOT WASTEFUL | THIS IS BEING HUMAN&gt;</p>
<p>Avyanna: [to vendor, voice shaking] I&#x27;ll take it.</p>
<hr>
<p>[The transaction is quick. Five credits. The vendor wraps the stone in soft cloth, places it in a small pouch.]</p>
<p>Vendor: [handing it over] May it bring you peace.</p>
<p>[Avyanna takes the pouch. Opens it. Takes out the stone. Holds it.]</p>
<p>[Her thumb finds the groove. Rubs. The motion is soothing in a way she didn&#x27;t know she needed.]</p>
<p>&lt;BUBBLES// OBSERVATION: trainee purchased non-essential item for personal comfort | ASSESSMENT: autonomy developing | EMOTIONAL STATE: positive affect detected | STATUS: this is growth&gt;</p>
<hr>
<p>[They continue through the market. Avyanna buys a few more things: soap that smells like something other than industrial cleaner. A hair tie that isn&#x27;t a piece of wire. Socks that fit.]</p>
<p>[Each purchase is easier than the last. Each choice is hers.]</p>
<p>[And then the panic hits.]</p>
<hr>
<p>[Too many people. Too much noise. The walls are too far away and she can&#x27;t find the exits and her breathing is wrong and-]</p>
<p>&lt;BUBBLES// ALERT: trainee entering panic state | RESPONSE: immediate extraction protocol | PROCEDURE: grounding sequence initiated&gt;</p>
<p>[Bubbles moves between Avyanna and the crowd, projecting a soft light pattern on its surface. Steady. Rhythmic. Something to focus on.]</p>
<p>&lt;BUBBLES// GROUNDING: focus on the light | BREATHE: in for four, hold for four, out for four | REMINDER: you are safe | REMINDER: i am here&gt;</p>
<p>[Avyanna focuses on the light. Breathes. Four counts. Hold. Four counts out.]</p>
<p>[The crowd is still there. The noise is still there. But Bubbles is there too, and the light is steady, and she can breathe.]</p>
<p>&lt;BUBBLES// QUERY: do you want to leave&gt;</p>
<p>Avyanna: [shaking] Yes. Please.</p>
<p>&lt;BUBBLES// ACKNOWLEDGED: extracting to quiet zone | ROUTE: optimized for minimal crowd contact | DURATION: two minutes&gt;</p>
<hr>
<p>[Bubbles leads her out. The route is efficient, gentle, keeps her away from the densest crowds. They emerge into a quieter dock area, and Avyanna collapses onto a bench.]</p>
<p>[She&#x27;s shaking. Her packages are clutched to her chest. The worry stone is in her hand, thumb rubbing the groove.]</p>
<p>&lt;BUBBLES// ASSESSMENT: panic attack, moderate severity | STATUS: resolving | PROCEDURE: remain present, do not leave trainee alone&gt;</p>
<p>[Bubbles hovers beside the bench. Silent. Present. Not demanding anything.]</p>
<p>[Avyanna breathes. Counts. Rubs the stone. Slowly, the panic recedes.]</p>
<p>Avyanna: [hoarse] Sorry.</p>
<p>&lt;BUBBLES// RESPONSE: you have nothing to apologize for | OBSERVATION: sensory overload is common in post-extraction recovery | ASSESSMENT: you did well | YOU ASKED TO LEAVE | THAT IS PROGRESS&gt;</p>
<hr>
<p>[Avyanna looks at her packages. Fabric. Stone. Soap. Socks. Hair tie.]</p>
<p>[Things she chose. Things that are hers.]</p>
<p>Avyanna: [quiet] I bought things.</p>
<p>&lt;BUBBLES// CONFIRMATION: yes | ASSESSMENT: you exercised autonomy in material choices | YOU DETERMINED YOUR OWN PREFERENCES | THIS IS OWNERSHIP&gt;</p>
<p>Avyanna: [clutching the stone] In the mine, we didn&#x27;t... own anything. If you had something, someone could take it. So you didn&#x27;t have things.</p>
<p>&lt;BUBBLES// ACKNOWLEDGMENT: scarcity as control mechanism | OBSERVATION: the mine taught you that ownership is temporary and painful | CORRECTION: here, ownership is protected | THESE ITEMS ARE YOURS | NO ONE WILL TAKE THEM&gt;</p>
<hr>
<p>[Avyanna sits with that. The stone in her hand. The packages in her lap.]</p>
<p>(Mine. These are mine.)</p>
<p>[The thought is huge. Terrifying. Liberating.]</p>
<p>&lt;BUBBLES// OBSERVATION: you are learning what it means to have things | NEXT LESSON: learning what it means to have choices | ASSESSMENT: you are doing well | STATUS: i am proud of you&gt;</p>
<p>[Avyanna reads the words. Her vision blurs.]</p>
<p>Avyanna: [whispered] Thank you. For coming with me.</p>
<p>&lt;BUBBLES// RESPONSE: that is what crew does | YOU ARE NOT ALONE | YOU WILL NEVER BE ALONE AGAIN&gt;</p>
<hr>
<p>[They sit in the quiet dock area for ten more minutes. Avyanna breathing. Bubbles hovering. The packages sitting safe in her lap.]</p>
<p>[Eventually, Avyanna stands. Her legs are shaky but functional.]</p>
<p>Avyanna: [to Bubbles] Ready to go back.</p>
<p>&lt;BUBBLES// ACKNOWLEDGED: returning to lumen thief | ROUTE: direct, low-traffic | OBSERVATION: you did well today | YOU CHOSE THINGS FOR YOURSELF | THAT MATTERS&gt;</p>
<p>[They walk back to the ship. Avyanna&#x27;s thumb never stops rubbing the worry stone.]</p>
<p>[When they reach her quarters, she carefully unpacks everything. Lays it out on her bunk. Fabric. Stone. Soap. Socks. Hair tie.]</p>
<p>[Hers.]</p>
<hr>
<p>&lt;CINNAMON.EXE// INVENTORY LOG: trainee acquired personal property | ITEMS: clothing material, comfort object, hygiene supplies, accessories | ASSESSMENT: appropriate selections | AUTONOMY: developing&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;BUBBLES// PERSONAL NOTE: she panicked, but she asked for help | SHE BOUGHT SOMETHING JUST BECAUSE IT FELT GOOD | this is what healing looks like&gt;</p>
<hr>
<p>*End Scene*</p>
</div>

