:: Act1 10b Roster Roles And Refusal
<h1>Optional 10b: Roster Roles And Refusal</h1>
<p class="source-note">Source: 10b_roster_roles_and_refusal.md</p>
<div class="scene-prose">
<p>&gt; **[SCENE - OCCURS POST-CH10, FIRST WEEK ABOARD]** &gt; *Location: Atrium / Commons message board* &gt; *Present: Avyanna, Bubbles, Cinnamon.exe (Waffle cameo)* &gt; *Teaching: how the ship uses roles without cages; how to refuse without debt-math*</p>
<hr>
<p>[The atrium looks like a public square that got lost inside a ship.]</p>
<p>[A wall of screens. A board covered in handwritten notes and printed forms. A rack of tools that are treated like they belong to everyone.]</p>
<p>[Avyanna stands close enough to read but not close enough to be accused of wanting.]</p>
<p>(If I stand too close, someone will notice and decide I need a job.)</p>
<p>[Bubbles drifts in beside her, a soft whir of fans and servo-corrections.]</p>
<p>Bubbles: You are reading the roster.</p>
<p>Avyanna: [quick] I wasn&#x27;t- I just-</p>
<p>[She stops herself.]</p>
<p>[Elia taught her this: don&#x27;t spend breath paying for a harmless action.]</p>
<p>Avyanna: I am reading it.</p>
<p>[Bubbles pauses-an AI version of approval that doesn&#x27;t try to look like a smile.]</p>
<p>&lt;BUBBLES// OBSERVATION: corrected speech pattern | INFERENCE: trainee adopting non-apology | CONFIDENCE: 0.83&gt;</p>
<p>Bubbles: Good.</p>
<p>[The roster is color-coded. Not names, not ranks. Tasks.]</p>
<p>[*Bridge watch.*]</p>
<p>[*Galley sanitation.*]</p>
<p>[*Medbay inventory.*]</p>
<p>[*Cargo checks.*]</p>
<p>[*&quot;Sparkles&quot; review.*]</p>
<p>[Next to each: a little note stamped in a hand that looks like it enjoys rules.]</p>
<p>&gt; **ASSIGNED** / **VOLUNTEERED** / **PENDING**</p>
<p>Avyanna: [frowning] Why does it say pending.</p>
<p>[Cinnamon&#x27;s interface lights on the nearest terminal, text crisp as a knife.]</p>
<p>&lt;CINNAMON.EXE// EXPLANATION: tasks require consent | NOTE: assignment without consent is &quot;order&quot; | ORDER is not default on this ship&gt;</p>
<p>Avyanna: [quiet] But... things have to get done.</p>
<p>&lt;CINNAMON.EXE// RESPONSE: yes | FOLLOW-UP: &quot;done&quot; is not the same as &quot;taken&quot;&gt;</p>
<p>[Bubbles bumps the edge of the board with one rotor, almost gentle.]</p>
<p>Bubbles: Sometimes the task waits.</p>
<p>Avyanna: That seems... inefficient.</p>
<p>Bubbles: Correct.</p>
<p>Bubbles: We still do it.</p>
<p>[Avyanna looks down at a section titled CREW ROLES.]</p>
<p>[*Captain.*]</p>
<p>[*Second.*]</p>
<p>[*Pilot.*]</p>
<p>[*Investigator.*]</p>
<p>[*Medical.*]</p>
<p>[*Heavy.*]</p>
<p>[*Citizens.*]</p>
<p>[She flinches at the word the mine used-ASSET-and finds it nowhere.]</p>
<p>(No one owns me here. They keep saying it like I can just... accept it.)</p>
<p>Avyanna: If there&#x27;s a captain, isn&#x27;t that... hierarchy.</p>
<p>[Bubbles tilts, a micro-correction like shrugging.]</p>
<p>Bubbles: There is leadership.</p>
<p>Bubbles: There is not ownership.</p>
<p>&lt;CINNAMON.EXE// CLARIFICATION: &quot;captain&quot; = accountability handle | NOT &quot;captain&quot; = entitlement to bodies&gt;</p>
<p>Avyanna: [reading] &quot;If you do not understand a task, you may refuse.&quot;</p>
<p>Avyanna: That&#x27;s... written down.</p>
<p>&lt;CINNAMON.EXE// OBSERVATION: trainee surprise at explicit permissions | INFERENCE: prior environment punished questions | CONFIDENCE: 0.92&gt;</p>
<p>[The board has a second line beneath it, in messier handwriting.]</p>
<p>&gt; **If you refuse, you are still crew.**</p>
<p>[Avyanna stares at that until her eyes sting.]</p>
<p>Avyanna: What if refusing gets someone hurt.</p>
<p>[Bubbles&#x27; fans shift. A sound like a small sigh.]</p>
<p>Bubbles: Then we discuss it.</p>
<p>Avyanna: In the mine, refusal was... a cost.</p>
<p>&lt;CINNAMON.EXE// RESPONSE: on this ship, refusal is information&gt;</p>
<p>Bubbles: And information prevents injury.</p>
<p>[Avyanna&#x27;s throat tightens. She swallows it down.]</p>
<p>Avyanna: So I can say no.</p>
<p>Bubbles: Yes.</p>
<p>Avyanna: And no one- [she can&#x27;t finish the sentence, because saying it out loud feels like inviting it]</p>
<p>&lt;CINNAMON.EXE// COMPLETION: no penalty&gt;</p>
<p>[The words sit there on the screen, plain and unornamented.]</p>
<p>[No penalty.]</p>
<p>[Avyanna reads it twice.]</p>
<p>Avyanna: [small] That&#x27;s a lie in most places.</p>
<p>&lt;CINNAMON.EXE// ACKNOWLEDGEMENT: correct&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;WAFFLE.BAT// INTERRUPTION: it is a lie elsewhere | HERE it is a policy | POLICY is enforceable by civic annoyance&gt;</p>
<p>[Waffle&#x27;s text appears with a little bat icon, like it&#x27;s proud of being a problem.]</p>
<p>Avyanna: Civic annoyance.</p>
<p>&lt;WAFFLE.BAT// DEFINITION: if someone punishes you for refusal, we punish them for punishing you&gt;</p>
<p>[Bubbles rotates a fraction, as if to say: yes, that.]</p>
<p>Bubbles: This is how communities function.</p>
<p>[Avyanna points to a line item: GALLEY SANITATION.]</p>
<p>Avyanna: Does someone get punished for not doing that.</p>
<p>&lt;CINNAMON.EXE// RESPONSE: no | NOTE: consequences may include: smell | communal disappointment | Elia&#x27;s dramatic commentary&gt;</p>
<p>Avyanna: Who enforces it.</p>
<p>[Bubbles&#x27; fans change pitch: pleased.]</p>
<p>Bubbles: You are learning.</p>
<p>Avyanna: [dry, surprised at herself] I&#x27;m trying.</p>
<p>&lt;CINNAMON.EXE// ADDENDUM: attempting is sufficient | PROGRESS TRACKING: consistent&gt;</p>
<p>[Avyanna looks back at the roster.]</p>
<p>[A new item appears at the bottom, stamped PENDING.]</p>
<p>&gt; **TRAINEE: AVYANNA - OPTIONAL: LIBRARY ORIENTATION**</p>
<p>[Avyanna stiffens on instinct.]</p>
<p>Avyanna: Optional means... trap.</p>
<p>&lt;CINNAMON.EXE// CORRECTION: optional means optional&gt;</p>
<p>Bubbles: Do you want to go.</p>
<p>[Avyanna hesitates.]</p>
<p>(Do I want anything yet. Or do I just want to not be punished.)</p>
<p>Avyanna: I want... to see it.</p>
<p>Bubbles: Then we go.</p>
<p>[No ceremony. No test. Just motion.]</p>
<p>[Avyanna follows, and the ship does not demand payment for curiosity.]</p>
<hr>
<p>[They don&#x27;t go to the library.]</p>
<p>[Not yet.]</p>
<p>[Bubbles stops at a terminal alcove beside the board. Cinnamon&#x27;s interface is already open, a blank form waiting like a mouth.]</p>
<p>Avyanna: What&#x27;s that.</p>
<p>&lt;CINNAMON.EXE// ANSWER: practice&gt;</p>
<p>[A new message appears on the screen, stamped with urgency that looks official on purpose.]</p>
<p>&gt; **NOTICE** &gt; Report to medbay immediately. &gt; Failure to comply will be noted.</p>
<p>[Avyanna&#x27;s body moves before her mind does.]</p>
<p>[Her spine goes rigid. Her tongue prepares a yes.]</p>
<p>[She catches herself with both hands on the counter.]</p>
<p>Avyanna: [tight] Who sent that.</p>
<p>&lt;CINNAMON.EXE// RESPONSE: me&gt;</p>
<p>[Avyanna&#x27;s breath punches out.]</p>
<p>Avyanna: You-</p>
<p>&lt;CINNAMON.EXE// CLARIFICATION: simulation | PURPOSE: teach refusal without punishment&gt;</p>
<p>[Bubbles drifts closer.]</p>
<p>Bubbles: This is a drill.</p>
<p>Avyanna: [quiet] Drills are still... real in the body.</p>
<p>Bubbles: Correct.</p>
<p>Bubbles: That is why we drill.</p>
<p>&lt;CINNAMON.EXE// INSTRUCTION: apply three questions&gt;</p>
<p>Avyanna: [swallowing] What. Why. What if.</p>
<p>Avyanna: What: &quot;Report to medbay.&quot;</p>
<p>Avyanna: Why: unknown.</p>
<p>Avyanna: What if I don&#x27;t: &quot;noted.&quot; Not... specified.</p>
<p>&lt;CINNAMON.EXE// AFFIRMATION: correct&gt;</p>
<p>[Avyanna lifts her gaze to the terminal, to the lie that looks like authority.]</p>
<p>Avyanna: Under which jurisdiction.</p>
<p>&lt;CINNAMON.EXE// RESPONSE: internal ship message board&gt;</p>
<p>Avyanna: Enforced by whom.</p>
<p>&lt;CINNAMON.EXE// RESPONSE: no enforcement mechanism exists&gt;</p>
<p>[Her mouth is dry.]</p>
<p>Avyanna: So I can... ignore it.</p>
<p>Bubbles: Yes.</p>
<p>Avyanna: Or ask.</p>
<p>Bubbles: Yes.</p>
<p>[A second line appears beneath the notice, like a footnote that learned to bite.]</p>
<p>&gt; *If this is urgent, reply with: WHAT IS THE EMERGENCY.*</p>
<p>[Avyanna reads it twice.]</p>
<p>Avyanna: That&#x27;s allowed.</p>
<p>&lt;CINNAMON.EXE// ANSWER: yes&gt;</p>
<p>Avyanna: [testing the muscle] What is the emergency.</p>
<p>&lt;CINNAMON.EXE// RESPONSE: none&gt;</p>
<p>[Her shoulders drop a fraction.]</p>
<p>Avyanna: [quiet] That feels... impossible.</p>
<p>Bubbles: It is merely unfamiliar.</p>
<p>[Waffle&#x27;s icon pops up.]</p>
<p>&lt;WAFFLE.BAT// COMMENTARY: you are doing it | CHAOS SCORE: 2/10 | DISAPPOINTMENT: mild&gt;</p>
<p>Avyanna: [startled laugh] What.</p>
<p>&lt;WAFFLE.BAT// EXPLANATION: chaos is educational | HOWEVER: this is healthy boring&gt;</p>
<hr>
<p>[Cinnamon opens another template.]</p>
<p>&gt; **REFUSAL RECORD (INTERNAL)** &gt; *Request:* &gt; *Your response:* &gt; *Reason (optional):* &gt; *Follow-up action:*</p>
<p>Avyanna: You keep records of... no.</p>
<p>&lt;CINNAMON.EXE// AFFIRMATION: yes&gt;</p>
<p>Avyanna: Why.</p>
<p>&lt;CINNAMON.EXE// EXPLANATION: patterns | NOTE: if someone repeatedly &quot;requests&quot; in coercive shapes, we notice&gt;</p>
<p>[Avyanna&#x27;s stomach twists.]</p>
<p>Avyanna: So if someone starts acting like Aurum-</p>
<p>Bubbles: We notice.</p>
<p>Bubbles: Early.</p>
<p>Avyanna: And then.</p>
<p>&lt;WAFFLE.BAT// ANSWER: then we get annoying&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;BUBBLES// ADDENDUM: then we protect you&gt;</p>
<p>[Avyanna stares at that.]</p>
<p>(Protect. Not own.)</p>
<p>Avyanna: Do you... record when I say yes too.</p>
<p>&lt;CINNAMON.EXE// RESPONSE: only when &quot;yes&quot; affects safety | NOTE: consent records are not ownership records&gt;</p>
<p>Avyanna: Consent records.</p>
<p>Bubbles: You are allowed to have a history that no one can edit without effort.</p>
<p>[The sentence lands like a door that locks from the inside.]</p>
<hr>
<p>[Avyanna looks back up at the board.]</p>
<p>[At the &quot;sparkles&quot; section-complaints and suggestions, filed like civic petitions.]</p>
<p>Avyanna: Are those... real.</p>
<p>Bubbles: Yes.</p>
<p>Avyanna: People complain.</p>
<p>Bubbles: Frequently.</p>
<p>Avyanna: And no one-</p>
<p>&lt;CINNAMON.EXE// COMPLETION: retaliates&gt;</p>
<p>[Avyanna swallows.]</p>
<p>Avyanna: That&#x27;s... a lot of trust.</p>
<p>&lt;CINNAMON.EXE// RESPONSE: trust is built by enforcing it&gt;</p>
<p>Avyanna: Who enforces it.</p>
<p>[Bubbles tilts.]</p>
<p>Bubbles: Us.</p>
<p>&lt;WAFFLE.BAT// ADDENDUM: and also social disapproval&gt;</p>
<p>Avyanna: [soft] Civic annoyance.</p>
<p>&lt;WAFFLE.BAT// AFFIRMATION: civic annoyance&gt;</p>
<p>[Avyanna looks at the empty space on the board where her own note could go, someday.]</p>
<p>(A voice that doesn&#x27;t have to be purchased.)</p>
<p>[She doesn&#x27;t post yet.]</p>
<p>[But she stands there long enough that the ship records the possibility and doesn&#x27;t demand payment for it either.]</p>
</div>

* [[Continue to Chapter 11: Shard Whispers->Act1 11 Shard Whispers]]
