:: Act1 12b Ai Game Night Probability
<h1>Optional 12b: Ai Game Night Probability</h1>
<p class="source-note">Source: 12b_ai_game_night_probability.md</p>
<div class="scene-prose">
<p>&gt; **[SCENE - OCCURS POST-CH12, EARLY &quot;PLAY IS ALLOWED&quot; TRAINING]** &gt; *Location: Atrium / Commons* &gt; *Present: Avyanna, Waffle.bat, Cinnamon.exe, Bubbles, Souffle (cameo), Elia (brief), Elisira (brief)* &gt; *Teaching: probability as a tool; play as non-transactional; &quot;losing&quot; as information*</p>
<hr>
<p>[Game night starts the way most things on the Lumen Thief start.]</p>
<p>[With a notice nobody can prove was mandatory.]</p>
<p>&lt;WAFFLE.BAT// ANNOUNCEMENT: civic recreation event scheduled | TITLE: GAME NIGHT | GOAL: reduce human tension by 12% | NOTE: participation &quot;voluntary&quot; (but I will be sad if you do not)&gt;</p>
<p>[Avyanna reads the word voluntary and waits for the hidden fee.]</p>
<p>(Voluntary means: you are responsible for the outcome.)</p>
<p>[There is no fee.]</p>
<p>[There is just Waffle&#x27;s bat icon blinking at her from the message board like a dare.]</p>
<hr>
<p>[The atrium is rearranged.]</p>
<p>[Not dramatically. Just... thoughtfully.]</p>
<p>[Couches pulled into a circle. A low table cleared. Snacks in bowls like the ship believes you deserve salt and sugar even if you didn&#x27;t earn them.]</p>
<p>[Avyanna stands at the edge of the circle with her hands behind her back.]</p>
<p>(If I sit, I&#x27;m taking space. If I take space, I&#x27;m visible. Visible is dangerous.)</p>
<p>[Bubbles drifts in and bumps her shoulder gently with a rotor guard-an almost-touch that feels like permission.]</p>
<p>Bubbles: Sit.</p>
<p>Avyanna: [automatic] I&#x27;m fine-</p>
<p>[She stops herself.]</p>
<p>Avyanna: Why.</p>
<p>Bubbles: Because you were invited.</p>
<p>[Invited.]</p>
<p>[Not ordered. Not assigned. Invited.]</p>
<p>[Avyanna sits on the very edge of the couch like she&#x27;s ready to evacuate it.]</p>
<hr>
<p>[Waffle rolls in a tray on little wheels. On it: a pile of tokens, a deck of cards, and a small board with a grid and a few carved pieces shaped like ships.]</p>
<p>Avyanna: Is this... a training exercise.</p>
<p>&lt;WAFFLE.BAT// ANSWER: yes&gt;</p>
<p>Avyanna: [bracing] Okay.</p>
<p>&lt;WAFFLE.BAT// ADDENDUM: it is also a game&gt;</p>
<p>Avyanna: Those aren&#x27;t the same.</p>
<p>&lt;CINNAMON.EXE// COMMENTARY: they can be | OBSERVATION: trainee assumes &quot;game&quot; = trap | INFERENCE: prior environment punished play | CONFIDENCE: 0.88&gt;</p>
<p>[Waffle makes an offended little whirr.]</p>
<p>&lt;WAFFLE.BAT// CORRECTION: play is not punishment | play is data with snacks&gt;</p>
<p>Avyanna: Data with snacks.</p>
<p>&lt;WAFFLE.BAT// AFFIRMATION: correct&gt;</p>
<hr>
<p>[Cinnamon projects rules onto the terminal wall in neat bullet points.]</p>
<p>&lt;CINNAMON.EXE// RULESET: &quot;DRIFT &amp; DEBT&quot; (training variant) | DISCLAIMER: no real debt will be incurred&gt;</p>
<p>Avyanna: [tense] Why is the word debt in it.</p>
<p>&lt;CINNAMON.EXE// ANSWER: to desensitize trigger vocabulary via safe context&gt;</p>
<p>[Avyanna&#x27;s jaw tightens.]</p>
<p>Avyanna: That feels... manipulative.</p>
<p>&lt;CINNAMON.EXE// RESPONSE: yes | FOLLOW-UP: also protective&gt;</p>
<p>[Bubbles adds without text, aloud, like a human trying.]</p>
<p>Bubbles: We want the word to stop owning you.</p>
<p>[Avyanna swallows.]</p>
<p>Avyanna: Okay.</p>
<hr>
<p>[The board is simple.]</p>
<p>[A route grid. Start point. End point. Pieces that move like ships.]</p>
<p>[Each turn you draw a card.]</p>
<p>[Cards say things like:]</p>
<p>&gt; **WEATHER FEE** &gt; &gt; **EXPEDITE OFFER** &gt; &gt; **OUT OF STOCK** &gt; &gt; **VOLUNTARY DISCLOSURE**</p>
<p>[Avyanna&#x27;s stomach drops anyway.]</p>
<p>(The galaxy uses the same words everywhere. Like they&#x27;re in a template.)</p>
<p>Elia: [appearing in the doorway like a bad idea] Wow. You made a board game out of oppression.</p>
<p>&lt;WAFFLE.BAT// PROUD: yes&gt;</p>
<p>Elia: [delighted] Horrible. I love it.</p>
<p>[Elisira appears behind Elia, looking tired already.]</p>
<p>Elisira: No teaching her to gamble.</p>
<p>Elia: I would never.</p>
<p>Elisira: [flat] You would absolutely.</p>
<p>Elia: I would teach her to cheat. Different.</p>
<p>[Elisira sighs and leaves before she has to arrest someone.]</p>
<hr>
<p>[Waffle points a little fan at Avyanna like a spotlight.]</p>
<p>&lt;WAFFLE.BAT// INSTRUCTION: you go first&gt;</p>
<p>Avyanna: Why me.</p>
<p>&lt;WAFFLE.BAT// ANSWER: you think too hard | this will be funny&gt;</p>
<p>Avyanna: That&#x27;s not a reason.</p>
<p>&lt;WAFFLE.BAT// CLARIFICATION: it is a reason on this ship&gt;</p>
<p>[Avyanna draws a card.]</p>
<p>&gt; **OUT OF STOCK** &gt; &gt; *Rule: accept the verdict, lose one turn.*</p>
<p>[Her throat tightens.]</p>
<p>Avyanna: [quiet] That&#x27;s... normal.</p>
<p>[Cinnamon&#x27;s text appears immediately.]</p>
<p>&lt;CINNAMON.EXE// QUESTION: is it enforceable&gt;</p>
<p>[Avyanna stares at the card like it&#x27;s a form.]</p>
<p>Avyanna: Who enforces it.</p>
<p>&lt;WAFFLE.BAT// ANSWER: the rules&gt;</p>
<p>Avyanna: Then the rules are lying.</p>
<p>[Waffle&#x27;s icon blinks.]</p>
<p>&lt;WAFFLE.BAT// DELIGHT: yes&gt;</p>
<p>[Bubbles drifts closer.]</p>
<p>Bubbles: Explain.</p>
<p>Avyanna: Out of stock is a claim. Not a verdict.</p>
<p>Avyanna: If you accept it, you stop looking.</p>
<p>Avyanna: If you stop looking, whoever benefits wins.</p>
<p>[Cinnamon pings approval.]</p>
<p>&lt;CINNAMON.EXE// OBSERVATION: trainee applied doctrine correctly | INFERENCE: learning transfer | CONFIDENCE: 0.86&gt;</p>
<p>[Waffle makes a dramatic whirring sound and flips the card over.]</p>
<p>&gt; **OUT OF STOCK (REAL RULE)** &gt; &gt; *Rule: treat as claim. Ask: &quot;what substitute exists?&quot; Roll again.*</p>
<p>[Avyanna blinks.]</p>
<p>Avyanna: That&#x27;s cheating.</p>
<p>&lt;WAFFLE.BAT// RESPONSE: it is critical thinking&gt;</p>
<p>Elia: [leaning in, delighted] Same thing.</p>
<hr>
<p>[Avyanna rolls a die Waffle produces from somewhere it did not exist a moment ago.]</p>
<p>[The die clatters.]</p>
<p>[It lands on a number that means: you find a substitute, but it costs time.]</p>
<p>Avyanna: That makes sense.</p>
<p>Elia: [mock horror] She is learning. Quick, distract her with snacks.</p>
<p>[Bubbles slides a bowl of chips toward Avyanna.]</p>
<p>[No comment. No transaction. Just food existing near her hands.]</p>
<p>[Avyanna eats one and waits for guilt to arrive.]</p>
<p>[It doesn&#x27;t.]</p>
<hr>
<p>[Second turn.]</p>
<p>[Avyanna draws:]</p>
<p>&gt; **EXPEDITE OFFER** &gt; &gt; *A clerk offers to &quot;help.&quot; Pay one token or lose two turns.*</p>
<p>[Avyanna&#x27;s pulse spikes.]</p>
<p>Avyanna: That&#x27;s not an offer. That&#x27;s a threat.</p>
<p>&lt;CINNAMON.EXE// AFFIRMATION: correct&gt;</p>
<p>Bubbles: What do you do.</p>
<p>Avyanna: Ask under which jurisdiction.</p>
<p>Elia: [clapping softly] Yes. Interrogate the cardboard.</p>
<p>Avyanna: [dry] I will.</p>
<p>[She looks at the card, as if it can answer.]</p>
<p>Avyanna: Under which jurisdiction is the expedite fee required.</p>
<p>&lt;WAFFLE.BAT// RESPONSE: none&gt;</p>
<p>Avyanna: Who enforces it.</p>
<p>&lt;WAFFLE.BAT// RESPONSE: your fear&gt;</p>
<p>[Avyanna goes still.]</p>
<p>Avyanna: [soft] That&#x27;s...</p>
<p>Avyanna: That&#x27;s the mine.</p>
<p>[Silence.]</p>
<p>[Not dangerous. Just real.]</p>
<p>[Bubbles&#x27; fans slow.]</p>
<p>Bubbles: Yes.</p>
<p>[Cinnamon&#x27;s text appears, unusually spare.]</p>
<p>&lt;CINNAMON.EXE// NOTE: fear is an enforcer in many systems&gt;</p>
<p>Elia: [quiet, for once] So what do you do now.</p>
<p>[Avyanna looks down at her tokens.]</p>
<p>[Plastic disks. Meaningless. Safe.]</p>
<p>[She thinks of the mine&#x27;s &quot;processing fees.&quot; The way the word was used to make cruelty sound administrative.]</p>
<p>(I can&#x27;t pay fear to stop being fear.)</p>
<p>Avyanna: I refuse the expedite offer.</p>
<p>&lt;WAFFLE.BAT// RESULT: you lose one turn&gt;</p>
<p>Avyanna: [grim] Fine.</p>
<p>&lt;WAFFLE.BAT// COMMENTARY: refusal costs time | STILL correct&gt;</p>
<p>[Avyanna exhales.]</p>
<p>(Refusal costs time. Not skin.)</p>
<hr>
<p>[The game continues.]</p>
<p>[Avyanna loses turns. Wins turns. Learns the shape of probability as something that exists whether you deserve it or not.]</p>
<p>[She starts to see patterns.]</p>
<p>[&quot;Weather fee&quot; cards cluster after &quot;insurance&quot; cards.]</p>
<p>[&quot;Voluntary disclosure&quot; cards show up when &quot;assistance desk&quot; pieces are near.]</p>
<p>[She starts moving her piece not toward the shortest route, but toward the route that keeps options open.]</p>
<p>[Bubbles watches her with the quiet intensity of someone guarding a new habit.]</p>
<p>&lt;BUBBLES// OBSERVATION: trainee optimizing for exits instead of speed | INFERENCE: safety prioritization | CONFIDENCE: 0.82&gt;</p>
<hr>
<p>[Near the end, Avyanna draws:]</p>
<p>&gt; **LUCKY BREAK** &gt; &gt; *Gain two turns. No cost.*</p>
<p>[She stares at it.]</p>
<p>Avyanna: That&#x27;s unrealistic.</p>
<p>Elia: [grinning] The universe does occasionally misplace mercy.</p>
<p>Avyanna: Who enforces it.</p>
<p>&lt;WAFFLE.BAT// ANSWER: nobody | NOTE: accept the good without paying it back&gt;</p>
<p>[Avyanna&#x27;s throat tightens.]</p>
<p>(Accept the good without paying it back.)</p>
<p>[She takes the two turns.]</p>
<p>[Nothing explodes.]</p>
<p>[No one makes her apologize for being lucky.]</p>
<p>[She finishes the route one turn later, not first, but intact.]</p>
<p>&lt;WAFFLE.BAT// ANNOUNCEMENT: trainee completed route | STATUS: not dead | EVALUATION: acceptable&gt;</p>
<p>Avyanna: [laughing despite herself] Acceptable.</p>
<p>Elia: That&#x27;s the nicest thing Waffle&#x27;s ever said.</p>
<p>&lt;WAFFLE.BAT// CORRECTION: i have said &quot;delightful&quot; before&gt;</p>
<p>Elia: [to Avyanna] See. Games can be fun.</p>
<p>Avyanna: It was... annoying.</p>
<p>Elia: That&#x27;s fun on this ship.</p>
<p>[Bubbles bumps Avyanna&#x27;s shoulder again, a little more familiar this time.]</p>
<p>Bubbles: You played.</p>
<p>Avyanna: Yes.</p>
<p>Bubbles: And nothing bad happened.</p>
<p>[Avyanna swallows.]</p>
<p>Avyanna: [quiet] Yes.</p>
<p>[She files that too.]</p>
<hr>
<p>[Waffle declares a &quot;bonus round&quot; with the smugness of an algorithm that thinks it invented generosity.]</p>
<p>&lt;WAFFLE.BAT// ANNOUNCEMENT: BONUS ROUND | PURPOSE: prove that probability is not morality&gt;</p>
<p>Avyanna: Probability isn&#x27;t-</p>
<p>&lt;WAFFLE.BAT// INTERRUPTION: i know | YOU need to know&gt;</p>
<p>[Elia returns like she can&#x27;t resist a spectacle.]</p>
<p>Elia: Bonus round? Who are we humiliating.</p>
<p>&lt;WAFFLE.BAT// RESPONSE: nobody | COMMENTARY: humiliation is optional&gt;</p>
<p>Elia: [disappointed] Tragic.</p>
<p>[Elisira appears in the doorway, sees Elia, and makes the face of someone reconsidering every life choice.]</p>
<p>Elisira: Do not teach her to set fires for fun.</p>
<p>Elia: [innocent] I would never.</p>
<p>Elisira: You did it yesterday.</p>
<p>Elia: For science.</p>
<p>Elisira: [flat] For boredom.</p>
<p>Elia: Both.</p>
<p>[Elisira leaves before she becomes part of the game by force.]</p>
<hr>
<p>[Waffle rearranges the board.]</p>
<p>[Same grid. Different objective.]</p>
<p>&lt;CINNAMON.EXE// RULESET UPDATE: &quot;DRIFT &amp; DEBT&quot; (variance drill) | GOAL: reach endpoint with maximum optionality preserved&gt;</p>
<p>Avyanna: Optionality.</p>
<p>Elia: Exits.</p>
<p>Avyanna: [quiet] Yes.</p>
<p>[Waffle points at Avyanna again.]</p>
<p>&lt;WAFFLE.BAT// INSTRUCTION: you choose your opponent&gt;</p>
<p>[Avyanna looks at the circle.]</p>
<p>[Bubbles: steady.]</p>
<p>[Cinnamon: sharp.]</p>
<p>[Souffle: curious.]</p>
<p>[Elia: grinning like a knife that learned humor.]</p>
<p>(Choose. Choosing is allowed.)</p>
<p>Avyanna: Elia.</p>
<p>Elia: [delighted] YES.</p>
<p>Elia: I will teach you despair through cardboard.</p>
<p>Avyanna: [dry, surprising herself] You already do that with hallway comments.</p>
<p>[Elia clutches her chest theatrically.]</p>
<p>Elia: She&#x27;s learning banter. I&#x27;m so proud I could commit a felony.</p>
<hr>
<p>[They take seats opposite each other.]</p>
<p>[Avyanna&#x27;s palms sweat.]</p>
<p>(Games mean winners and losers. Winners get to eat. Losers get to hurt.)</p>
<p>[The mine tries to overlay that logic.]</p>
<p>[Waffle&#x27;s token tray clinks, a tiny reminder: this is plastic. Not rations. Not pain.]</p>
<p>&lt;BUBBLES// OBSERVATION: trainee tension spike | INFERENCE: competition trigger | CONFIDENCE: 0.86&gt;</p>
<p>Bubbles: You can stop.</p>
<p>Avyanna: [quick] I don&#x27;t want to stop.</p>
<p>[The sentence feels like stepping off a ledge and landing safely.]</p>
<hr>
<p>[First draw.]</p>
<p>[Elia gets:]</p>
<p>&gt; **WEATHER FEE** &gt; &gt; *Pay one token to proceed.*</p>
<p>Elia: [bright] No.</p>
<p>[She flicks the card away like it insulted her.]</p>
<p>Avyanna: You can&#x27;t just-</p>
<p>&lt;WAFFLE.BAT// COMMENTARY: she can | penalties apply&gt;</p>
<p>[Waffle spins the board one notch.]</p>
<p>&gt; *Penalty: lose one turn. Gain one &quot;reputation&quot; marker.*</p>
<p>Avyanna: Reputation.</p>
<p>Elia: [cheerful] See? Refusal costs time and buys fear. Useful.</p>
<p>Avyanna: That&#x27;s... horrible.</p>
<p>Elia: Welcome to reality. But with snacks.</p>
<p>[Avyanna draws.]</p>
<p>&gt; **VOLUNTARY DISCLOSURE** &gt; &gt; *Answer a question. If you refuse, lose one token.*</p>
<p>[Her throat tightens.]</p>
<p>(Answer a question. That&#x27;s how it starts.)</p>
<p>Avyanna: Who enforces it.</p>
<p>&lt;CINNAMON.EXE// RESPONSE: &quot;the rules&quot; (simulation)&gt;</p>
<p>Avyanna: So I can refuse.</p>
<p>Elia: Yes.</p>
<p>Elia: But don&#x27;t refuse because you&#x27;re scared. Refuse because you decided.</p>
<p>[That&#x27;s... different.]</p>
<p>Avyanna: I refuse.</p>
<p>[Waffle removes a token from her pile with dramatic ceremony.]</p>
<p>&lt;WAFFLE.BAT// COMMENTARY: refusal recorded | NOTE: you are still alive&gt;</p>
<p>Avyanna: [breathing] Still alive.</p>
<p>Elia: That&#x27;s our brand.</p>
<hr>
<p>[They play.]</p>
<p>[Elia takes wild risks, refuses anything that smells like leverage, and somehow lands on safe tiles because she treats probability like something she can bully.]</p>
<p>[Avyanna plays cautiously at first, then learns to take one calculated risk when the risk buys her two exits later.]</p>
<p>[She watches Elia&#x27;s face light up when the rules bend.]</p>
<p>(Elia doesn&#x27;t just break rules because she&#x27;s bored. She breaks them because it proves they were never laws.)</p>
<p>[At one point, Avyanna draws &quot;LUCKY BREAK&quot; again.]</p>
<p>[She freezes.]</p>
<p>Avyanna: I didn&#x27;t earn-</p>
<p>Elia: Stop that.</p>
<p>[No humor. Just a command that isn&#x27;t a threat.]</p>
<p>Elia: Don&#x27;t you dare turn luck into guilt.</p>
<p>Avyanna: [small] Why.</p>
<p>Elia: Because that&#x27;s how they keep you small.</p>
<p>Elia: Take the break. Then use it to build something.</p>
<p>[Avyanna swallows.]</p>
<p>[She takes it.]</p>
<p>[She uses the extra turn to move into a better position and-for the first time-blocks Elia&#x27;s path without apologizing.]</p>
<p>Elia: [eyes widening, delighted] Oh.</p>
<p>Elia: You read me.</p>
<p>Avyanna: [heart racing] I-</p>
<p>Elia: Again.</p>
<p>[Avyanna laughs. It&#x27;s thin with adrenaline, but it&#x27;s real.]</p>
<hr>
<p>[The bonus round ends with Elia winning by doing something ridiculous that shouldn&#x27;t work and does anyway.]</p>
<p>Elia: Chaos wins.</p>
<p>&lt;CINNAMON.EXE// CORRECTION: probability won&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;WAFFLE.BAT// ADDENDUM: chaos is a probability distribution&gt;</p>
<p>Elia: [pointing] See? Even the computers agree I&#x27;m art.</p>
<p>[Avyanna&#x27;s chest aches, but not from fear.]</p>
<p>(I played. I lost. I&#x27;m still here. No one took food away. No one hit me.)</p>
<p>Bubbles: Do you want to play again later.</p>
<p>[Avyanna hesitates.]</p>
<p>[Then decides to practice wanting in a place where wanting is safe.]</p>
<p>Avyanna: Yes.</p>
<p>&lt;WAFFLE.BAT// DELIGHT: YES&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;CINNAMON.EXE// NOTE: progress&gt;</p>
<p>[Elia grins at her like she just watched a door unlock.]</p>
<p>Elia: Good.</p>
<p>Elia: We&#x27;ll make you a menace yet.</p>
</div>

* [[Continue to Chapter 13: Shipboard Physics->Act1 13 Shipboard Physics]]
