:: Act1 13e Water Is Not A Test
<h1>Optional 13e: Water Is Not A Test</h1>
<p class="source-note">Source: 13e_water_is_not_a_test.md</p>
<div class="scene-prose">
<p>&gt; **[SCENE - OCCURS POST-CH13d, EARLY REST PRACTICE]** &gt; *Location: Crew quarters washroom / laundry nook* &gt; *Present: Avyanna, Bubbles, Cinnamon.exe* &gt; *Teaching: comfort is not a quota; care is not a reward*</p>
<hr>
<p>[The washroom is too clean.]</p>
<p>[Not sterile-lived clean. The kind of clean that means someone uses this space and then puts it back the way they want to find it.]</p>
<p>[Avyanna stands in the doorway with her hands in fists, staring at the shower control panel.]</p>
<p>[A dial with temperature ranges. A toggle for pressure. A little display that says WATER AVAILABLE.]</p>
<p>(Available for who. For how long.)</p>
<p>[Bubbles hovers behind her, not pushing her in.]</p>
<p>Bubbles: You have not bathed.</p>
<p>Avyanna: [too fast] I have.</p>
<p>[Bubbles waits.]</p>
<p>[Avyanna hears herself and corrects the lie without being asked.]</p>
<p>Avyanna: I rinsed.</p>
<p>Avyanna: Once.</p>
<p>Bubbles: That is not bathing.</p>
<p>Avyanna: It was enough.</p>
<p>&lt;BUBBLES// OBSERVATION: deflection language | INFERENCE: scarcity conditioning | CONFIDENCE: 0.89&gt;</p>
<p>[Avyanna stares at the dial.]</p>
<p>[She can feel the mine on her skin like a second uniform: dust that never leaves, sweat that dries wrong, the memory of water that came with eyes on you.]</p>
<p>(If you take too long, someone yells. If you take too much, someone takes it back.)</p>
<p>[Cinnamon&#x27;s terminal in the corner wakes, as if it has been listening and decides it is time to be useful.]</p>
<p>&lt;CINNAMON.EXE// STATUS: water rationing not active | NOTE: no metering policy for hygiene | POLICY: &quot;take what you need&quot;&gt;</p>
<p>Avyanna: [hoarse] Nothing is unmetered.</p>
<p>&lt;CINNAMON.EXE// RESPONSE: correct in hostile systems | NOTE: this ship is not hostile to hygiene&gt;</p>
<p>Avyanna: That doesn&#x27;t mean it&#x27;s safe.</p>
<p>[Bubbles rotates toward her, fans quieting.]</p>
<p>Bubbles: You are safe enough to be clean.</p>
<p>[The sentence lands like a hand offered.]</p>
<p>[Avyanna doesn&#x27;t take it. Not yet.]</p>
<p>Avyanna: If I use too much, does it... affect the ship.</p>
<p>[Cinnamon answers without pity, which is the only way Avyanna can hear it.]</p>
<p>&lt;CINNAMON.EXE// ANSWER: negligible impact | CONTEXT: hygiene is operational requirement | FOLLOW-UP: infections cost more water&gt;</p>
<p>Avyanna: [a small laugh that isn&#x27;t humor] Everything is operational.</p>
<p>&lt;CINNAMON.EXE// AFFIRMATION: yes&gt;</p>
<p>Bubbles: We like you operational.</p>
<p>Avyanna: [quiet] I&#x27;m not a machine.</p>
<p>[Bubbles&#x27; fans change pitch-annoyed in defense of her.]</p>
<p>Bubbles: Correct.</p>
<p>Bubbles: You are a person.</p>
<p>[Avyanna swallows.]</p>
<p>[She reaches for the dial and stops.]</p>
<p>[Her hand hovers over warmth like it&#x27;s a trap door.]</p>
<p>(Warm water means vulnerability. Warm water means someone can hurt you because you&#x27;re soft.)</p>
<p>Avyanna: [barely] How long.</p>
<p>Bubbles: How long what.</p>
<p>Avyanna: How long until I&#x27;m... done.</p>
<p>[Silence. Listening, not judging.]</p>
<p>&lt;CINNAMON.EXE// OBSERVATION: trainee framing hygiene as timed task | INFERENCE: prior punishment context | CONFIDENCE: 0.91&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;CINNAMON.EXE// RESPONSE: there is no &quot;until&quot; | SUGGESTION: bathe until body reports &quot;better&quot;&gt;</p>
<p>Avyanna: My body lies.</p>
<p>[Bubbles drifts closer, just enough that Avyanna can hear the tiny corrective hum.]</p>
<p>Bubbles: Your body is a witness.</p>
<p>Bubbles: It is scared. It is still a witness.</p>
<p>[Avyanna&#x27;s throat tightens.]</p>
<p>Avyanna: That&#x27;s not fair.</p>
<p>Bubbles: No.</p>
<p>Bubbles: The mine was not fair.</p>
<p>[Avyanna turns the dial one notch toward warm.]</p>
<p>[Water hisses through the pipes like the ship clearing its throat.]</p>
<p>[She flinches at the sound.]</p>
<p>[Bubbles does not comment.]</p>
<p>[The first spray hits her palm-hot enough to make her jerk back.]</p>
<p>Avyanna: Ow.</p>
<p>&lt;CINNAMON.EXE// OBSERVATION: temperature overshoot | ACTION: reduce to safe threshold&gt;</p>
<p>[The water shifts to a steady warmth, like someone smoothing a blanket.]</p>
<p>Avyanna: [suspicious] You adjusted it.</p>
<p>&lt;CINNAMON.EXE// AFFIRMATION: yes | NOTE: you are allowed to be comfortable&gt;</p>
<p>[Avyanna stares at the display again.]</p>
<p>[WATER AVAILABLE.]</p>
<p>[It doesn&#x27;t tick down.]</p>
<p>(It doesn&#x27;t tick down.)</p>
<p>[Her shoulders drop by a millimeter.]</p>
<p>[She steps in.]</p>
<p>[The water hits her hair, her scalp, her neck. Heat spreads under skin that has been cold for too long.]</p>
<p>[For a second, the mine tries to rise-showers as a line, as a punishment, as a place where eyes measured you for weakness.]</p>
<p>[Avyanna&#x27;s lungs seize.]</p>
<p>[She turns her face into the spray and forces breath through the moment.]</p>
<p>[In. Out.]</p>
<p>[In.]</p>
<p>[Bubbles speaks from outside the curtain, not entering without permission.]</p>
<p>Bubbles: Do you want company.</p>
<p>Avyanna: [immediate] No.</p>
<p>[Then-because she is learning honesty is a floor, not a threat-]</p>
<p>Avyanna: Thank you.</p>
<p>Bubbles: You are welcome.</p>
<p>[Cinnamon&#x27;s text appears on the terminal, simple.]</p>
<p>&lt;CINNAMON.EXE// REMINDER: you may take two towels&gt;</p>
<p>Avyanna: [startled] Two.</p>
<p>&lt;CINNAMON.EXE// CLARIFICATION: yes | NOTE: drying quickly reduces chill response&gt;</p>
<p>[She laughs again, quieter.]</p>
<p>Avyanna: Who decided that.</p>
<p>&lt;CINNAMON.EXE// ANSWER: me&gt;</p>
<p>Avyanna: [muttering] Of course.</p>
<p>[She washes. Slowly.]</p>
<p>[Soap that smells like something alive-not mine disinfectant, not chemical fear.]</p>
<p>[When she finally turns the water off, she stands still for a moment, waiting for the other shoe.]</p>
<p>[No alarm.]</p>
<p>[No banging on the door.]</p>
<p>[No shouted quota.]</p>
<p>[Just the ship humming like it has always been this kind.]</p>
<p>[Avyanna steps out wrapped in a towel that is too soft to trust.]</p>
<p>[Bubbles offers another without making it a question that costs anything.]</p>
<p>[Avyanna takes it.]</p>
<p>[Her hands tremble once.]</p>
<p>(I&#x27;m clean. And nothing bad happened.)</p>
<p>[She doesn&#x27;t know what to do with that.]</p>
<p>[So she does the only thing she knows how to do with new evidence.]</p>
<p>[She files it.]</p>
<hr>
<p>[The laundry nook is adjacent, like the ship assumes hygiene includes clothing and isn&#x27;t making you ask permission twice.]</p>
<p>[A row of baskets. A machine that looks too expensive to waste on ordinary fabric. Shelves of detergent in small bottles, each labeled with a scent name that feels like a luxury someone bothered to catalog.]</p>
<p>[Avyanna stands in front of them as if choosing wrong will be punished.]</p>
<p>(In the mine, you got whatever chemical soap they issued. It stripped skin. It didn&#x27;t count as cruelty because it was &quot;standard.&quot;)</p>
<p>[Bubbles hovers at the doorway again, refusing to enter without being invited.]</p>
<p>Bubbles: Laundry is next.</p>
<p>Avyanna: [stiff] I can do it.</p>
<p>Bubbles: Yes.</p>
<p>Bubbles: Do you want help.</p>
<p>[Avyanna&#x27;s throat tightens at the question. Help always meant debt.]</p>
<p>Avyanna: No.</p>
<p>[Then-]</p>
<p>Avyanna: Maybe... explain the machine.</p>
<p>[Bubbles&#x27; fans shift: approval without fanfare.]</p>
<p>Bubbles: Yes.</p>
<hr>
<p>[The machine has a simple interface.]</p>
<p>[*Load.*]</p>
<p>[*Select cycle.*]</p>
<p>[*Select temperature.*]</p>
<p>[*Start.*]</p>
<p>[No cost display. No countdown. No warning about &quot;overuse.&quot;]</p>
<p>Avyanna: [quiet] It doesn&#x27;t track.</p>
<p>&lt;CINNAMON.EXE// RESPONSE: it tracks for maintenance only | NOTE: not for punishment&gt;</p>
<p>[Avyanna pulls her clothes from the hamper.]</p>
<p>[Crew-issue fabric, already softening from regular washing.]</p>
<p>[She hesitates at the pile, suddenly aware of how much she owns.]</p>
<p>(Mine brain: hoard. Keep. Don&#x27;t waste. Don&#x27;t take what you can&#x27;t defend.)</p>
<p>[She starts sorting like she&#x27;s trying to prove she deserves it.]</p>
<p>[Bubbles doesn&#x27;t let her spiral quietly.]</p>
<p>Bubbles: You are permitted to wash all of it.</p>
<p>Avyanna: [defensive] I wasn&#x27;t-</p>
<p>Bubbles: You were.</p>
<p>[Avyanna freezes.]</p>
<p>Avyanna: [small] If I wash it all, I&#x27;ll have nothing to wear.</p>
<p>&lt;CINNAMON.EXE// SUGGESTION: use spare linens | NOTE: crew-issue basics exist in supply locker | POLICY: you may take them&gt;</p>
<p>Avyanna: Supply locker.</p>
<p>(The mine would never let you take from supply without &quot;approval.&quot; Approval meant debt.)</p>
<p>Bubbles: We can get you two sets of basics.</p>
<p>Avyanna: Two.</p>
<p>Bubbles: Two.</p>
<p>[Bubbles pauses.]</p>
<p>Bubbles: You can have more later.</p>
<p>[Avyanna&#x27;s chest tightens.]</p>
<p>Avyanna: [rough] I don&#x27;t know how to...</p>
<p>Bubbles: Want.</p>
<p>[The word is gentle and brutal.]</p>
<p>[Avyanna swallows.]</p>
<p>Avyanna: I don&#x27;t know how to want without paying.</p>
<p>&lt;CINNAMON.EXE// RESPONSE: practice&gt;</p>
<hr>
<p>[Avyanna stares at the detergent shelf again.]</p>
<p>Avyanna: What do I pick.</p>
<p>&lt;CINNAMON.EXE// QUESTION: what do you prefer&gt;</p>
<p>[Prefer.]</p>
<p>[The word feels like a trick question.]</p>
<p>[Avyanna picks up one bottle, reads the label.]</p>
<p>&gt; *Citrus.*</p>
<p>[She puts it down.]</p>
<p>[Picks up another.]</p>
<p>&gt; *Lavender.*</p>
<p>[Her throat tightens unexpectedly.]</p>
<p>(The mine smelled like metal and sweat and disinfectant. Lavender smells like a place where no one dies for production.)</p>
<p>Avyanna: [quiet] This one.</p>
<p>[No alarm. No correction. No laughter.]</p>
<p>Bubbles: Acknowledged.</p>
<p>&lt;CINNAMON.EXE// NOTE: preference logged | COMMENTARY: good&gt;</p>
<p>[&quot;Preference logged&quot; should feel invasive.]</p>
<p>[Instead it feels like someone taking her seriously.]</p>
<hr>
<p>[She loads the machine.]</p>
<p>[Presses start.]</p>
<p>[The drum begins to turn.]</p>
<p>[The sound is ordinary. Domestic. It makes her eyes sting.]</p>
<p>(The ship is doing chores. The ship is treating me like I belong inside chores.)</p>
<p>[Avyanna wipes her face with the edge of her towel before she can be embarrassed by needing one.]</p>
<p>[Bubbles stays outside the doorway, a sentinel for dignity.]</p>
<p>Bubbles: Do you need anything else.</p>
<p>[Avyanna looks at the shelf of folded towels.]</p>
<p>[One is still around her hair. Another around her shoulders. She wants a third, absurdly, because it would mean she&#x27;s allowed to be wasteful.]</p>
<p>[She takes a breath.]</p>
<p>Avyanna: I... want another towel.</p>
<p>[Silence.]</p>
<p>[Then Cinnamon, brisk as ever:]</p>
<p>&lt;CINNAMON.EXE// RESPONSE: granted&gt;</p>
<p>[Bubbles adds:]</p>
<p>Bubbles: I will bring it.</p>
<p>[Avyanna&#x27;s throat tightens. Not with shame. With something worse.]</p>
<p>(They didn&#x27;t make me justify it.)</p>
<p>[Bubbles returns with a third towel and places it on the counter like it&#x27;s nothing.]</p>
<p>[Like wanting is nothing.]</p>
<p>[Avyanna doesn&#x27;t know how to hold that without breaking, so she does what she&#x27;s learned to do with fragile things.]</p>
<p>[She holds it carefully.]</p>
</div>

