:: Act1 13g Rho Kenna Coffee
<h1>Optional 13g: Rho Kenna Coffee</h1>
<p class="source-note">Source: 13g_rho_kenna_coffee.md</p>
<div class="scene-prose">
<p>&gt; **[INTERSTITIAL - OCCURS POST-CH13b]** &gt; *Trigger: Rho&#x27;s coffee is care, not just habit* &gt; *Purpose: show Rho&#x27;s &quot;governance&quot; started as love*</p>
<hr>
<p>[Rho makes coffee like he&#x27;s sealing a hull breach.]</p>
<p>[Measured. Repeated. Mildly furious at physics.]</p>
<p>[Avyanna watches from the galley doorway with the same caution she uses around armed strangers.]</p>
<p>[Not because Rho is dangerous.]</p>
<p>[Because tenderness is.]</p>
<p>Rho: [without looking up] You going to stare all day or drink something.</p>
<p>Avyanna: I&#x27;m not staring.</p>
<p>Rho: You&#x27;re staring.</p>
<p>[He sets a mug on the counter and slides it toward her.]</p>
<p>[No ceremony. No &quot;you earned it.&quot; No invoice tone.]</p>
<p>Avyanna: [quiet] Why do you care so much.</p>
<p>Rho: About coffee.</p>
<p>Avyanna: About... making it right.</p>
<p>[Rho&#x27;s hand pauses mid-stir.]</p>
<p>[A small stillness, like a door shutting gently.]</p>
<p>Rho: Habit.</p>
<p>[The word is true and not true.]</p>
<hr>
<p>## Intercut - *Grasp of Dawn* (Rho&#x27;s First Shift)</p>
<p>[The galley is smaller.]</p>
<p>[The ship is smaller too-old metal, cheap insulation, a floor that rattles when the engines push.]</p>
<p>[Rho is younger and not yet tired in the particular ways that never go away.]</p>
<p>[He is holding a mug with both hands like it&#x27;s a promise.]</p>
<p>[Across from him, Kenna sits cross-legged on the bench seat, hair tied back with a strip of wire because she is an engineer and everything becomes a tool.]</p>
<p>Kenna: That is not coffee.</p>
<p>Rho: [defensive] It&#x27;s hot.</p>
<p>Kenna: That&#x27;s not the definition.</p>
<p>[Kenna leans over his shoulder and adjusts the grinder setting with gentle violence.]</p>
<p>Rho: Don&#x27;t.</p>
<p>Kenna: I&#x27;m helping.</p>
<p>Rho: You always say that like it&#x27;s a legal defense.</p>
<p>Kenna: [mouth twitching] It is.</p>
<hr>
<p>[Kenna watches the brew drip, eyes half-lidded like she&#x27;s listening to the ship&#x27;s bones.]</p>
<p>Kenna: You&#x27;re scared.</p>
<p>Rho: I&#x27;m fine.</p>
<p>Kenna: That&#x27;s also not the definition.</p>
<p>[Rho exhales.]</p>
<p>Rho: New job.</p>
<p>Kenna: I read the contract.</p>
<p>Rho: I read it too.</p>
<p>Kenna: [flat] Then you&#x27;re scared on purpose.</p>
<p>[Rho looks away.]</p>
<p>Kenna: Hey.</p>
<p>[Her hand hovers near his wrist.]</p>
<p>[She doesn&#x27;t grab.]</p>
<p>[She waits for consent like it&#x27;s normal.]</p>
<p>Rho: Yes.</p>
<p>[Kenna touches him, steady pressure, not a claim.]</p>
<p>Kenna: If it goes bad, we leave.</p>
<p>Rho: The paperwork-</p>
<p>Kenna: [sharp] The paperwork doesn&#x27;t get to kill us.</p>
<p>[Rho&#x27;s throat tightens.]</p>
<p>Rho: I don&#x27;t want to lose the crew.</p>
<p>Kenna: Then feed them.</p>
<p>Rho: [confused] What.</p>
<p>Kenna: You do this.</p>
<p>[She points at the coffee.]</p>
<p>Kenna: You make something small and normal and yours.</p>
<p>Kenna: You make the ship feel like a place people come back to.</p>
<p>Kenna: That&#x27;s governance.</p>
<p>[Rho makes a face.]</p>
<p>Rho: You sound like Rowan.</p>
<p>Kenna: I sound like someone who wants you alive.</p>
<hr>
<p>[Kenna tastes the coffee, then nods once-approval that lands like a medal.]</p>
<p>Kenna: Better.</p>
<p>Rho: You fixed it.</p>
<p>Kenna: I corrected your assumptions.</p>
<p>Rho: That&#x27;s the same thing.</p>
<p>Kenna: It is not.</p>
<p>Kenna: But I love that you tried.</p>
<p>[Rho laughs, startled by how easy it is.]</p>
<p>[Kenna smiles like she did that on purpose.]</p>
<hr>
<p>## Return - Galley (Now)</p>
<p>[Rho&#x27;s hand resumes stirring like the pause never happened.]</p>
<p>[Avyanna watches his face for grief.]</p>
<p>[He gives her none.]</p>
<p>Rho: Drink it before it dies.</p>
<p>Avyanna: Coffee dies.</p>
<p>Rho: Everything dies.</p>
<p>[A beat.]</p>
<p>Rho: This is just faster.</p>
<p>[Avyanna lifts the mug.]</p>
<p>[It smells like bitter warmth and competence.]</p>
<p>Avyanna: [soft] It&#x27;s good.</p>
<p>[Rho grunts like he doesn&#x27;t know what to do with praise.]</p>
<p>Rho: That&#x27;s because I&#x27;m excellent.</p>
<p>[He is not smiling.]</p>
<p>[He is, somehow, making the galley feel like a place people come back to.]</p>
<hr>
<p>*End Chapter 13g*</p>
</div>

