:: Act1 14c Bridge Transit Ritual
<h1>Optional 14c: Bridge Transit Ritual</h1>
<p class="source-note">Source: 14c_bridge_transit_ritual.md</p>
<div class="scene-prose">
<p>&gt; **[SCENE - OCCURS POST-CH14, FIRST REAL TRANSIT]** &gt; *Location: Bridge / corridor approach* &gt; *Present: Full crew (bridge rotation), AI citizens via telemetry* &gt; *Teaching: travel is work; fear is handled as procedure; usefulness is a job, not a personality*</p>
<hr>
<p>[The bridge smells like coffee and ozone and focus.]</p>
<p>[Jalen sits in the pilot cradle, spine straight, hands light on the controls like anything heavier would insult the ship.]</p>
<p>[Elisira stands behind them with a slate, posture relaxed in the way that means she is not relaxed.]</p>
<p>[Vesper has one hand on a rail and the other on a datapad full of forms that never stop wanting signatures.]</p>
<p>[Rho leans in the doorway with a mug and the expression of someone prepared to fight the universe with caffeine.]</p>
<p>[Elia is sprawled near weapons control, boots on a brace, looking bored on purpose.]</p>
<p>[Avyanna takes the last open station and tries not to look like she is begging to be allowed to exist there.]</p>
<p>(Bridge means responsibility. Responsibility means they can be angry at you.)</p>
<p>Jalen: [without looking back] Strap in.</p>
<p>[Avyanna straps in immediately.]</p>
<p>[Then stops herself.]</p>
<p>[Elia&#x27;s drill rises like a reflex with teeth.]</p>
<p>Avyanna: [careful] Why.</p>
<p>[Jalen&#x27;s mouth twitches. Not quite a smile.]</p>
<p>Jalen: Because this corridor is spiteful.</p>
<p>Elia: [bright] Because the map lies.</p>
<p>Elisira: Because the lane has been shifting.</p>
<p>Vesper: Because insurance pretends it&#x27;s weather.</p>
<p>Rho: Because if you hit a seam wrong, you bite your tongue off.</p>
<p>[Avyanna blinks.]</p>
<p>Avyanna: That&#x27;s... all the same answer.</p>
<p>Elia: Correct. Welcome to the galaxy.</p>
<hr>
<p>[Jalen taps the console. A route path blooms on the holo-blue line through blackness, annotated with numbers and warnings.]</p>
<p>&lt;CINNAMON.EXE// OBSERVATION: corridor stability rating &quot;marginal&quot; | NOTE: recommended speed reduction 12% | INFERENCE: reduced peak shear | CONFIDENCE: 0.84&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;WAFFLE.BAT// COMMENTARY: marginal is my favorite kind of safe&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;BUBBLES// REMINDER: keep limbs inside existence at all times&gt;</p>
<p>Elia: [to the air] Thank you, Bubbles. Very inspiring.</p>
<p>Bubbles: [over comm] You are welcome.</p>
<p>[The ship shifts. A subtle pressure change, like the universe leaning in to listen.]</p>
<p>[The stars on the forward display smear for a heartbeat.]</p>
<p>[Avyanna&#x27;s stomach drops.]</p>
<p>(Mine collapse.)</p>
<p>[The memory tries to overlay reality: rock groaning, dust filling lungs, the moment the ceiling decides to become ground.]</p>
<p>[Her hands clench on the armrests.]</p>
<p>[She counts exits without thinking.]</p>
<p>[There are none. It&#x27;s a bridge. It&#x27;s a box. It&#x27;s a trap.]</p>
<p>Vesper: [quiet, not looking at her] Check.</p>
<p>[Avyanna swallows.]</p>
<p>Avyanna: [too fast] Green.</p>
<p>[A beat.]</p>
<p>Avyanna: [correcting] Yellow.</p>
<p>[Vesper&#x27;s hand shifts-doesn&#x27;t touch her, just moves closer to the rail between them, a visible choice not to invade.]</p>
<p>Vesper: Thank you.</p>
<p>(Thank you for telling the truth. Not thank you for being okay.)</p>
<p>[Jalen&#x27;s voice stays calm, which is its own kind of weapon.]</p>
<p>Jalen: Drift left two degrees. Hold. Hold.</p>
<p>[The ship responds like it likes being spoken to with respect.]</p>
<p>[Pressure eases.]</p>
<p>[Avyanna&#x27;s lungs remember they are allowed to take air.]</p>
<p>Rho: [sipping] See. Fine.</p>
<p>&lt;CINNAMON.EXE// RESPONSE: &quot;fine&quot; is not a metric&gt;</p>
<p>Rho: [without missing a beat] &quot;Operationally adequate.&quot;</p>
<p>&lt;CINNAMON.EXE// ACCEPTABLE&gt;</p>
<hr>
<p>[A small shudder runs through the deck plates.]</p>
<p>[Not violent. Just... a seam.]</p>
<p>Elisira: [to Jalen] That was early.</p>
<p>Jalen: Yeah.</p>
<p>Jalen: [flat] The corridor is lying today.</p>
<p>Elia: [cheerful] I love it when the universe has personality.</p>
<p>Vesper: It&#x27;s not personality. It&#x27;s incentives.</p>
<p>Elia: [glancing over] Everything is incentives with you.</p>
<p>Vesper: [dry] Everything is incentives with everyone. Most people just don&#x27;t admit it.</p>
<p>[Avyanna watches them argue like it&#x27;s a ritual. No one is afraid of disagreement here.]</p>
<p>(In the mine, arguing meant punishment. Here it means... mapping.)</p>
<p>[Jalen flicks a switch. The display shifts-blue line, but now with a second overlay: a thin gray shadow of possible alternatives.]</p>
<p>Avyanna: What&#x27;s that.</p>
<p>Jalen: Official route.</p>
<p>Jalen: And what the ship thinks the route is.</p>
<p>Avyanna: [quiet] Those aren&#x27;t the same.</p>
<p>Jalen: [looking at her for the first time] Now you&#x27;re learning.</p>
<hr>
<p>[They ride the corridor like a river that dislikes boats.]</p>
<p>[Avyanna&#x27;s job is small.]</p>
<p>[Read out sensor warnings when Cinnamon flags them.]</p>
<p>[Repeat Elisira&#x27;s directions back so no one mishears.]</p>
<p>[Keep a log of time-stamps the way Vesper taught her: claim, source, when.]</p>
<p>[Useful. Quiet. Not invisible.]</p>
<p>[At one point, the ship lurches harder.]</p>
<p>[Avyanna&#x27;s vision narrows.]</p>
<p>[The mine tries to come back.]</p>
<p>[Rho&#x27;s voice cuts in, rough and real.]</p>
<p>Rho: Avy. Breathe.</p>
<p>[Avyanna inhales.]</p>
<p>[Jalen exhales at the same time-slow on purpose.]</p>
<p>[It pulls her rhythm with it, like gravity.]</p>
<p>[She holds on.]</p>
<p>[The corridor releases them with a final shiver, grudgingly.]</p>
<p>&lt;CINNAMON.EXE// OBSERVATION: stability improving | INFERENCE: seam passed | CONFIDENCE: 0.88&gt;</p>
<p>Elia: [stretching] That was disappointingly non-lethal.</p>
<p>Elisira: [without looking at her] We can arrange lethal if you&#x27;re bored.</p>
<p>Elia: [delighted] She loves me.</p>
<p>[Avyanna&#x27;s mouth twitches.]</p>
<p>[It&#x27;s almost a smile.]</p>
<p>[She files that too.]</p>
<hr>
<p>[Afterward, nobody disperses like they&#x27;re fleeing the smell of fear.]</p>
<p>[Jalen eases the ship down into a quiet stretch of corridor-space-stable enough to breathe, unstable enough to keep respect.]</p>
<p>Elisira: [to Avyanna] Debrief.</p>
<p>[Avyanna&#x27;s shoulders go rigid.]</p>
<p>(Debrief means you explain why you failed.)</p>
<p>Avyanna: I-</p>
<p>[Elisira waits, patient in the way that doesn&#x27;t let you hide behind panic.]</p>
<p>Avyanna: [working] We hit a seam early. The deck shuddered before the display predicted it. The pressure change came before the warning ping.</p>
<p>Elisira: Good.</p>
<p>Avyanna: Jalen adjusted two degrees left and reduced speed. Cinnamon flagged &quot;marginal&quot; stability, but it improved after the seam.</p>
<p>Elisira: What did your body do.</p>
<p>[Avyanna blinks.]</p>
<p>Avyanna: My body-</p>
<p>Vesper: [quiet] This is evidence too.</p>
<p>[Avyanna swallows.]</p>
<p>Avyanna: My hands clenched. I went cold. I... counted exits.</p>
<p>[Elia makes a small sound, not quite a joke.]</p>
<p>Elia: Same.</p>
<p>Avyanna: [startled] You count exits.</p>
<p>Elia: [bright] I count fun. Different category.</p>
<p>Elisira: [flat] Elia.</p>
<p>Elia: [innocent] I was validating.</p>
<p>[Avyanna&#x27;s mouth twitches again.]</p>
<p>[Rho drinks his coffee like it&#x27;s a shield and watches her carefully, as if counting how long it takes her to come back.]</p>
<p>Rho: You breathed when I told you.</p>
<p>Avyanna: Yes.</p>
<p>Rho: Good.</p>
<p>&lt;CINNAMON.EXE// OBSERVATION: trainee returned to baseline within 46 seconds | INFERENCE: recovery improving | CONFIDENCE: 0.81&gt;</p>
<p>[Avyanna looks at the telemetry and feels, unexpectedly, protected by being measured without being judged.]</p>
<p>Vesper: Log it.</p>
<p>Avyanna: [automatic] Yes.</p>
<p>[She catches herself.]</p>
<p>Avyanna: Why.</p>
<p>Vesper: Because next time your body tells you a story, we compare it to the data.</p>
<p>Vesper: If the story is wrong, we correct it. If the story is right, we prepare.</p>
<p>Avyanna: [quiet] Memory lies under stress.</p>
<p>Vesper: [a small nod] Exactly.</p>
<hr>
<p>[Later, in the corridor outside the bridge, Avyanna stops beside a wall panel and opens her notebook.]</p>
<p>[She writes in block letters, the way Vesper taught her to write claims:]</p>
<p>&gt; **CLAIM:** corridor seam occurred early &gt; &gt; **OBSERVATION:** deck shudder preceded warning ping &gt; &gt; **RESPONSE:** speed reduction + lateral correction &gt; &gt; **BODY:** cold, exit-counting, then recovery</p>
<p>[She stares at the last line.]</p>
<p>(Body: witness. Not enemy.)</p>
<p>[A shadow falls over the page.]</p>
<p>[Jalen stands there, hands in pockets, pretending this isn&#x27;t care.]</p>
<p>Jalen: You did fine.</p>
<p>Avyanna: [startled] Fine is not a metric.</p>
<p>[Jalen&#x27;s mouth twitches.]</p>
<p>Jalen: Operationally adequate.</p>
<p>Avyanna: [quiet] Better.</p>
<p>Jalen: Don&#x27;t make it a habit.</p>
<p>[They walk away before Avyanna can turn gratitude into a performance.]</p>
</div>

