:: Act1 15d Rival Crew Probe
<h1>Optional 15d: Rival Crew Probe</h1>
<p class="source-note">Source: 15d_rival_crew_probe.md</p>
<div class="scene-prose">
<p>&gt; **LUMEN THIEF - GUILD STATION NOTE (INTERNAL):** &gt; *Topic: curiosity is a form of targeting* &gt; *Rule: understate; let them remember their own assumptions*</p>
<hr>
<p>[The Guild concourse is loud in a way the mine never was.]</p>
<p>[The mine&#x27;s noise was work.]</p>
<p>[This noise is choice.]</p>
<p>[Vendors. Bounties. Arguments that end without blood.]</p>
<p>[People laughing like it doesn&#x27;t cost them.]</p>
<p>[Avyanna keeps her back to a support column and watches the flow of crews.]</p>
<p>[Not because she&#x27;s scared.]</p>
<p>[Because she learned that crowds are ledgers.]</p>
<p>[Everyone here has an invoice attached to their posture.]</p>
<hr>
<p>[The Lumen Thief crew draws eyes even when they try not to.]</p>
<p>[Not because they&#x27;re loud.]</p>
<p>[Because they don&#x27;t look like they&#x27;re hunting for permission.]</p>
<p>[Because Elia moves like she owns the air, and Elisira moves like the air asked her to.]</p>
<p>[Because Vesper&#x27;s stillness reads like a warning sign to anyone with sense.]</p>
<p>[Because Rho carries a parts crate like it weighs nothing and his eyes like it weighs everything.]</p>
<p>[Because the AIs talk where everyone can hear them and nobody shushes them.]</p>
<p>&lt;CINNAMON.EXE// OBSERVATION: external attention density elevated within 8m radius | INFERENCE: reputation gradient interacting with local rumor flow | CONFIDENCE: 0.74&gt;</p>
<hr>
<p>[Ten people approach in a loose wedge.]</p>
<p>[A full-sized crew.]</p>
<p>[Uniform jackets. Patches. Matching boots.]</p>
<p>[Roles visible even to Avyanna&#x27;s untrained eye: lead in front, two heavies, a tech, a pilot, a medic, an admin with a slate, and extra bodies for redundancy.]</p>
<p>[They are built to win by occupying space.]</p>
<p>[Avyanna recognizes the technique.]</p>
<p>[The mine did it with supervisors.]</p>
<p>[This is the same math in cleaner fabric.]</p>
<hr>
<p>Their Lead: [smiling] Lumen Thief.</p>
<p>[Not a greeting.]</p>
<p>[A label tossed like bait.]</p>
<p>Elia: [bright] Hi.</p>
<p>Their Admin: [pleasant, to Vesper] You&#x27;re the fixer, right.</p>
<p>Vesper: [mild] Define &quot;fixer.&quot;</p>
<p>Their Admin laughs like it&#x27;s a joke because admitting it isn&#x27;t would be rude.</p>
<p>Their Lead: We don&#x27;t mean anything by it. People talk.</p>
<p>Elisira: [flat] People always talk.</p>
<p>Their Lead: They say you take jobs nobody else can.</p>
<p>Rho: [dry] People say the corridor weather is natural.</p>
<p>Their Lead: [smile tightening] So it&#x27;s true.</p>
<p>Vesper: What&#x27;s your office.</p>
<p>Their Lead: Excuse me.</p>
<p>Vesper: Your office. Your authority. The thing you represent when you say &quot;we.&quot; Which jurisdiction are you trying to drag us into by talking to us like this.</p>
<p>[The lead&#x27;s smile wavers.]</p>
<p>Their Admin: We&#x27;re just contractors.</p>
<p>Elisira: That&#x27;s a credential. Not an office.</p>
<p>[The admin glances down at their slate. Not nervous. Logging.]</p>
<p>[Avyanna watches the motion and feels her skin crawl.]</p>
<p>(A list.)</p>
<hr>
<p>Their Lead: [recovering, to Avyanna] You&#x27;re new.</p>
<p>[He says it like an advantage.]</p>
<p>[Avyanna keeps her face neutral.]</p>
<p>Avyanna: Define &quot;new.&quot;</p>
<p>[Elia&#x27;s mouth twitches.]</p>
<p>[Elisira doesn&#x27;t look at Avyanna, but her posture shifts by a fraction: approval, filed.]</p>
<p>Their Lead: [laughing] Okay. Fair.</p>
<p>Their Lead: We heard you run a small crew.</p>
<p>Rho: We run a sufficient crew.</p>
<p>Their Lead: Seven bodies.</p>
<p>Their Pilot: [low] Plus their drones.</p>
<p>Their Medic: And the ship systems. You can&#x27;t count them as bodies.</p>
<p>Elia: [cheerful] You can if they yell at you.</p>
<p>&lt;WAFFLE.BAT// OBSERVATION: external crew attempting informal intimidation via headcount | COUNTERMEASURE: ignoring | CONFIDENCE: 0.92 | COMMENTARY: numbers are not competence&gt;</p>
<p>Their Tech: [to Cinnamon&#x27;s voice source] Is that your ship AI.</p>
<p>Cinnamon doesn&#x27;t answer questions from strangers.</p>
<p>Vesper: She has a name.</p>
<p>Their Tech: What is it.</p>
<p>Vesper: Not your business.</p>
<hr>
<p>[Their lead spreads their hands.]</p>
<p>Their Lead: We&#x27;re not trying to steal anything.</p>
<p>Their Lead: We&#x27;re offering to coordinate. Guild&#x27;s getting crowded. Contracts are getting weird. You know how it is.</p>
<p>Elisira: [flat] We do.</p>
<p>Their Lead: We can share intel. Share lanes. Keep from stepping on each other.</p>
<p>Rho: [dry] Define &quot;step.&quot;</p>
<p>Their Lead: [smile thinning again] You know. Compete.</p>
<p>Vesper: Then file a co-op agreement.</p>
<p>Their Lead: That&#x27;s-</p>
<p>Vesper: That&#x27;s how coordination works if you&#x27;re not trying to hide your leverage.</p>
<p>[The lead&#x27;s gaze slides to Avyanna again.]</p>
<p>Their Lead: How old are you.</p>
<p>[Silence drops like a tool hitting metal.]</p>
<p>[Not because the question is illegal.]</p>
<p>[Because it&#x27;s diagnostic.]</p>
<p>Vesper: [cold] Leave.</p>
<p>Their Lead: I&#x27;m not-</p>
<p>Elia: [still bright] She is.</p>
<p>Elia: You&#x27;re doing math in public.</p>
<p>Elia: We don&#x27;t like your math.</p>
<p>Their heavy shifts their weight.</p>
<p>[Elia smiles wider.]</p>
<p>[It isn&#x27;t friendly.]</p>
<p>It&#x27;s delighted.</p>
<p>Elia: If you want to learn how old she is, go ask the Guild for her file and see what they charge you.</p>
<p>Their Medic: [murmuring] That&#x27;s not fair.</p>
<p>Rho: [to the medic, almost kind] The galaxy isn&#x27;t.</p>
<p>Rho: That&#x27;s why we build floors anyway.</p>
<hr>
<p>[Their admin finally looks up from the slate.]</p>
<p>Their Admin: We&#x27;re not a threat.</p>
<p>Elisira: Then stop asking threat questions.</p>
<p>Their Admin: We were curious.</p>
<p>Elisira: Curiosity is not neutral.</p>
<p>Elisira: Curiosity is a direction you walk in.</p>
<hr>
<p>[The other crew backs up a step.]</p>
<p>[Not fear.]</p>
<p>[Calculation.]</p>
<p>[Elia is smiling.]</p>
<p>[Vesper is not.]</p>
<p>[Elisira looks like a locked door.]</p>
<p>[And the AIs are listening like witnesses.]</p>
<p>Ten bodies doesn&#x27;t feel like power anymore.</p>
<p>It feels like liability.</p>
<p>Their Lead: [hands up] Okay. Okay. Message received.</p>
<p>Their Lead: We&#x27;ll keep our distance.</p>
<p>Vesper: Good.</p>
<p>Their Lead: People are going to keep talking.</p>
<p>Vesper: They were going to anyway.</p>
<p>Their Lead: You&#x27;re not worried.</p>
<p>Rho: We&#x27;re always worried.</p>
<p>Rho: We just don&#x27;t let it run the ship.</p>
<hr>
<p>[The other crew leaves.]</p>
<p>[Ten bodies peeling away into the concourse noise.]</p>
<p>[Avyanna watches their admin&#x27;s slate as they go.]</p>
<p>[Not the writing. The habit.]</p>
<p>[The way they cataloged her like a salvage item.]</p>
<p>(Curiosity is targeting.)</p>
<p>[Elisira touches Avyanna&#x27;s elbow once as they fall back into motion.]</p>
<p>[Not a drag.]</p>
<p>[A check-in disguised as navigation.]</p>
<p>Elisira: Green.</p>
<p>Avyanna: [quiet] Green.</p>
<p>Elia: [cheerful] See.</p>
<p>Elia: We can do public spaces without murder. Growth.</p>
<p>Vesper: [dry] Don&#x27;t jinx it.</p>
<p>&lt;BUBBLES// OBSERVATION: trainee held boundary under social pressure | INFERENCE: integration improving | CONFIDENCE: 0.86 | NOTE: good work&gt;</p>
<p>[Avyanna doesn&#x27;t smile.]</p>
<p>[But she feels something settle in her chest.]</p>
<p>[Not safety.]</p>
<p>[A tool.]</p>
<p>[A script that isn&#x27;t obedience.]</p>
<hr>
<p>[As they pass a bounty board, Avyanna sees the reflection of the other crew&#x27;s lead watching them from across the concourse.]</p>
<p>[Not approaching.]</p>
<p>[Just... measuring.]</p>
<p>[Avyanna keeps walking.]</p>
<p>[She doesn&#x27;t look back.]</p>
<p>[She lets them keep their assumptions.]</p>
<p>[Because the ship taught her that being underestimated is sometimes the only affordable cloak.]</p>
</div>

