:: Act1 15e Maren Blocks
<h1>Optional 15e: Maren Blocks</h1>
<p class="source-note">Source: 15e_maren_blocks.md</p>
<div class="scene-prose">
<p>&gt; **[INTERSTITIAL - OCCURS POST-CH15]** &gt; *Trigger: Elisira teaches &quot;pattern&quot; like it&#x27;s a language* &gt; *Purpose: show Maren Sova&#x27;s foundation without confirming her fate*</p>
<hr>
<p>[Elisira&#x27;s lessons always look like paperwork until you realize they&#x27;re knives.]</p>
<p>[After the ghost net drill, Avyanna finds Elisira at the galley table with a small tin of colored blocks spread before her.]</p>
<p>[Not children&#x27;s toys.]</p>
<p>[Something more deliberate-hard-edged pieces, each one marked with a tiny notch.]</p>
<p>[Elisira sorts them into rows.]</p>
<p>[Blue.]</p>
<p>[Red.]</p>
<p>[Yellow.]</p>
<p>[Then she flips two pieces without changing her expression.]</p>
<p>[The whole row reads differently.]</p>
<p>Avyanna: [cautious] What is that.</p>
<p>Elisira: Encryption.</p>
<p>Avyanna: With blocks.</p>
<p>Elisira: With patterns.</p>
<p>[Avyanna watches her hands.]</p>
<p>[They&#x27;re steady.]</p>
<p>[Not the steady of calm.]</p>
<p>[The steady of someone who learned to survive by making systems behave.]</p>
<p>Avyanna: Who taught you.</p>
<p>[Elisira&#x27;s hands pause.]</p>
<p>[A beat too long.]</p>
<p>Elisira: Someone.</p>
<hr>
<p>## Intercut - Age Eleven (Maren&#x27;s Table)</p>
<p>[The apartment is small.]</p>
<p>[Station-small: air that tastes like recycled promises, walls thin enough that you can hear the neighbors&#x27; arguments through them.]</p>
<p>[Elisira sits at a table with her feet not quite reaching the floor.]</p>
<p>[Her hands are stained with marker ink.]</p>
<p>[Across from her, Maren Sova lays down three colored blocks like she&#x27;s dealing cards.]</p>
<p>Maren: Rule one.</p>
<p>Elisira: [automatic] Don&#x27;t trust a label.</p>
<p>[Maren&#x27;s mouth twitches.]</p>
<p>Maren: Good.</p>
<p>Maren: Rule two.</p>
<p>Elisira: Don&#x27;t trust a story.</p>
<p>Maren: Better.</p>
<p>Maren: Rule three.</p>
<p>[Elisira hesitates.]</p>
<p>[Maren waits.]</p>
<p>[Not impatient.]</p>
<p>[Just present, the way a good guardian is present-no pressure, no punishment, only expectation.]</p>
<p>Elisira: Trust the pattern.</p>
<p>Maren: Yes.</p>
<hr>
<p>[Maren taps the blocks.]</p>
<p>Maren: This is a message.</p>
<p>Elisira: It&#x27;s colors.</p>
<p>Maren: Colors are symbols.</p>
<p>Maren: Symbols become rules when someone enforces them.</p>
<p>Maren: Who enforces this.</p>
<p>Elisira: [frowning] You.</p>
<p>Maren: Here.</p>
<p>[Maren slides the blocks across the table, out of her own reach.]</p>
<p>Maren: Now who enforces it.</p>
<p>[Elisira stares.]</p>
<p>[The answer lands slow and bright.]</p>
<p>Elisira: Me.</p>
<p>[Maren nods.]</p>
<p>Maren: Good.</p>
<p>Maren: Remember that.</p>
<p>Maren: Most cages are built from things people agree to enforce for free.</p>
<hr>
<p>[Elisira&#x27;s throat tightens.]</p>
<p>Elisira: Why are you teaching me this.</p>
<p>Maren: Because you notice.</p>
<p>Maren: And because one day you&#x27;ll need to hide in plain sight.</p>
<p>Elisira: That sounds like leaving.</p>
<p>[Maren&#x27;s eyes flicker-too fast to be a confession, too slow to be nothing.]</p>
<p>Maren: It sounds like being prepared.</p>
<p>Elisira: Prepared for what.</p>
<p>Maren: [quiet] For a galaxy that lies.</p>
<hr>
<p>[Maren reaches over and brushes Elisira&#x27;s hair back from her forehead.]</p>
<p>[Touch offered, not taken.]</p>
<p>Maren: You can hate me if I disappear.</p>
<p>[Elisira freezes.]</p>
<p>Elisira: What.</p>
<p>Maren: You can decide I abandoned you.</p>
<p>Maren: If that story keeps you alive.</p>
<p>[Elisira&#x27;s eyes sting.]</p>
<p>Elisira: Don&#x27;t say that.</p>
<p>Maren: I&#x27;m saying it because I don&#x27;t get to control what you need later.</p>
<p>Maren: I only get to give you tools now.</p>
<hr>
<p>## Return - Galley (Now)</p>
<p>[Elisira&#x27;s fingers move again.]</p>
<p>[She flips a block.]</p>
<p>[The pattern changes.]</p>
<p>Avyanna: [quiet] Is it easier when it&#x27;s colors.</p>
<p>Elisira: It was.</p>
<p>Avyanna: Was.</p>
<p>[Elisira looks at her for one second.]</p>
<p>Elisira: It&#x27;s easier when the rules are honest.</p>
<p>Avyanna: The galaxy isn&#x27;t.</p>
<p>Elisira: [flat] Correct.</p>
<p>[Elisira turns a block over in her fingers, considering its weight.]</p>
<p>Elisira: That&#x27;s why we make our own.</p>
<p>[She pushes one block toward Avyanna.]</p>
<p>Elisira: Your turn.</p>
<p>[Avyanna hesitates.]</p>
<p>[Then she touches it.]</p>
<p>[Not a toy.]</p>
<p>[A tool.]</p>
<p>[A small, heavy proof that people can teach you how to disappear without telling you to vanish.]</p>
<hr>
<p>*End Chapter 15e*</p>
</div>

