:: Act1 16c Maintenance Pairing Day
<h1>Optional 16c: Maintenance Pairing Day</h1>
<p class="source-note">Source: 16c_maintenance_pairing_day.md</p>
<div class="scene-prose">
<p>&gt; **[SCENE - OCCURS POST-CH16b, FIRST MONTHLY MAINTENANCE RITUAL]** &gt; *Location: Ship-wide (pair rotations)* &gt; *Present: Avyanna + rotating crew; AI citizens coordinate* &gt; *Teaching: maintenance is care; tools are shared; no one is exempt*</p>
<hr>
<p>[Maintenance day starts with a board posted in the atrium.]</p>
<p>[Not a command. A schedule.]</p>
<p>[Pairs. Tasks. Time blocks.]</p>
<p>[Avyanna reads it twice before she believes her name belongs there.]</p>
<p>&gt; **AVYANNA + RHO** - *Filters / seals / coolant checks (galley-adjacent)* &gt; &gt; **AVYANNA + BUBBLES** - *Drone nest inventory (label sanity)* &gt; &gt; **AVYANNA + JALEN** - *Bridge conduit inspection (non-invasive)*</p>
<p>(They&#x27;re trusting me with the ship.)</p>
<p>[Cinnamon&#x27;s text appears on the terminal beside the board.]</p>
<p>&lt;CINNAMON.EXE// REMINDER: maintenance is preventative, not punitive | NOTE: you cannot &quot;fail&quot; maintenance if you report what you see&gt;</p>
<p>[Avyanna&#x27;s stomach tightens.]</p>
<p>(In the mine, maintenance meant blame.)</p>
<hr>
<p>[Rho meets her at the galley hatch with a tool bag and the expression of someone approaching a nuisance he loves anyway.]</p>
<p>Rho: You ever change a filter.</p>
<p>Avyanna: [honest] No.</p>
<p>Rho: Good. You won&#x27;t do it wrong on purpose then.</p>
<p>[He hands her gloves.]</p>
<p>[Not orders. Equipment.]</p>
<p>Rho: Rule one: tell me what you see. Not what you think you&#x27;re supposed to see.</p>
<p>Avyanna: [quiet] That sounds like Vesper.</p>
<p>Rho: Everybody on this ship is a little bit Vesper.</p>
<p>[He squints.]</p>
<p>Rho: Except Elia. Elia&#x27;s a whole different disease.</p>
<p>[Avyanna snorts.]</p>
<p>[They pop a panel. The smell of old air hits Avyanna&#x27;s face.]</p>
<p>[Rho points at the filter assembly.]</p>
<p>Rho: This is where &quot;out of stock&quot; likes to hide.</p>
<p>Avyanna: [frowning] Out of stock is-</p>
<p>Rho: A claim.</p>
<p>[He taps it with the back of a screwdriver.]</p>
<p>Rho: Not a verdict.</p>
<p>[Avyanna nods, cataloging it as a tool.]</p>
<p>[They work. Slowly.]</p>
<p>[Rho narrates the steps without making her feel stupid.]</p>
<p>[When Avyanna&#x27;s hand shakes, she pretends it&#x27;s from torque.]</p>
<p>[Rho doesn&#x27;t call her out.]</p>
<p>[He just steadies the panel with his own hand so she can use both hands without fear of dropping anything.]</p>
<hr>
<p>[Second rotation: drone nest inventory.]</p>
<p>[Bubbles is already there, surrounded by neat rows of parts that look like jewelry if you don&#x27;t know they can cut a man in half.]</p>
<p>Bubbles: Hello.</p>
<p>Avyanna: [more steady now] Hi.</p>
<p>[Bubbles projects an inventory list.]</p>
<p>Bubbles: We will count.</p>
<p>Avyanna: [dry] Counting as rebellion.</p>
<p>&lt;BUBBLES// AFFIRMATION: yes&gt;</p>
<p>[They move through bins.]</p>
<p>[Avyanna reads labels out loud.]</p>
<p>Avyanna: &quot;Swarm anchor pins.&quot;</p>
<p>Avyanna: &quot;Hinge washers.&quot;</p>
<p>Avyanna: &quot;Do not feed Elia.&quot;</p>
<p>[She stops.]</p>
<p>Avyanna: Is that a real category.</p>
<p>Bubbles: It is an aspirational category.</p>
<p>[Avyanna laughs.]</p>
<p>[The laugh feels like trespassing.]</p>
<p>[Bubbles doesn&#x27;t punish it.]</p>
<p>&lt;BUBBLES// OBSERVATION: trainee laughter | INFERENCE: nervous-system downshift | CONFIDENCE: 0.79&gt;</p>
<p>[They find a bin with a label crossed out and replaced in marker.]</p>
<p>&gt; **&quot;EXTRA&quot;** -&gt; **&quot;SPARE&quot;**</p>
<p>Avyanna: [soft] Someone changed it.</p>
<p>Bubbles: I did.</p>
<p>Avyanna: Why.</p>
<p>Bubbles: &quot;Extra&quot; implies waste.</p>
<p>Bubbles: &quot;Spare&quot; implies safety.</p>
<p>[Avyanna swallows.]</p>
<p>(Words matter. Always.)</p>
<hr>
<p>[Third rotation: bridge conduit inspection.]</p>
<p>[Jalen meets her in the corridor outside the bridge with a flashlight and a look that says: don&#x27;t touch anything, and also: you&#x27;re allowed to be here.]</p>
<p>Jalen: You&#x27;re not crawling in.</p>
<p>Avyanna: [relieved] Good.</p>
<p>Jalen: You&#x27;re observing.</p>
<p>Avyanna: That I can do.</p>
<p>[They open an access panel. Cables. Heat. A faint vibration that feels like the ship&#x27;s pulse.]</p>
<p>Jalen: See that discoloration.</p>
<p>Avyanna: [leaning in] Yes.</p>
<p>Jalen: What is it.</p>
<p>[Avyanna pauses.]</p>
<p>Avyanna: I don&#x27;t know.</p>
<p>[Jalen nods, as if &quot;I don&#x27;t know&quot; is a valid piece of evidence.]</p>
<p>Jalen: Good.</p>
<p>Jalen: Now tell me what you can say without guessing.</p>
<p>Avyanna: The sheath is worn. The color&#x27;s different near the joint. It looks... heated.</p>
<p>Jalen: Good.</p>
<p>Jalen: That&#x27;s a claim with observations behind it.</p>
<p>Avyanna: [startled] That&#x27;s Vesper language.</p>
<p>Jalen: Vesper stole it from physics. Physics stole it from reality.</p>
<hr>
<p>[By the time the last rotation ends, Avyanna&#x27;s hands are smudged with grease.]</p>
<p>[Her hair smells faintly like metal.]</p>
<p>[She&#x27;s tired in a way that doesn&#x27;t feel like punishment.]</p>
<p>(I worked. And no one took anything from me for it.)</p>
<p>[Back in the atrium, the board updates.]</p>
<p>&gt; **MAINTENANCE DAY - COMPLETE** &gt; &gt; *Notes: 3 issues logged. 0 blame assigned. 1 coffee spill archived for historical purposes.*</p>
<p>&lt;WAFFLE.BAT// COMMENTARY: coffee spill was heroic&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;CINNAMON.EXE// CORRECTION: coffee spill was avoidable&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;BUBBLES// ADDENDUM: coffee spill was forgiven&gt;</p>
<p>[Avyanna reads that and feels, for a moment, like she lives in a place where forgiveness is a default setting.]</p>
<p>[She doesn&#x27;t trust it yet.]</p>
<p>[But she&#x27;s learning how to stand on it anyway.]</p>
<hr>
<p>[The last entry on the board isn&#x27;t a task.]</p>
<p>&gt; **MAINTENANCE DAY DEBRIEF - OPTIONAL**</p>
<p>[Optional.]</p>
<p>[Avyanna&#x27;s eyes snag on the word like it&#x27;s a hook.]</p>
<p>(Optional means: you can choose. Choice means: you can be blamed.)</p>
<p>[She goes anyway.]</p>
<p>[The debrief is in the atrium, where people can hear and therefore things stay honest.]</p>
<p>[Elia lounges on a couch like meetings are allergic to her.]</p>
<p>[Elisira stands with her slate, already having organized everything into categories.]</p>
<p>[Rho smells like coolant and coffee.]</p>
<p>[Nyx is there too, hands stained with something that might be soil or ink.]</p>
<p>[Bubbles hovers. Cinnamon&#x27;s terminal glows. Waffle&#x27;s icon blinks like it&#x27;s trying to behave.]</p>
<p>Elisira: Issues logged.</p>
<p>[She reads without drama.]</p>
<p>Elisira: Galley filter assembly runs hot at joint. Bridge conduit sheath worn. Drone nest bin mislabeled.</p>
<p>Elia: [perking up] What.</p>
<p>Bubbles: The bin labeled &quot;do not feed Elia.&quot;</p>
<p>Elia: That&#x27;s an important label.</p>
<p>Elisira: It is not operationally necessary.</p>
<p>Elia: [affronted] It is culturally necessary.</p>
<p>&lt;CINNAMON.EXE// NOTE: both claims have merit&gt;</p>
<p>[Avyanna&#x27;s mouth twitches. It&#x27;s becoming a habit.]</p>
<p>Nyx: Did anyone get injured.</p>
<p>Rho: No.</p>
<p>Nyx: Good. That means maintenance did its job.</p>
<p>Avyanna: [quiet, before she can stop herself] In the mine, maintenance only happened after someone died.</p>
<p>[Silence.]</p>
<p>[Not the kind that punishes. The kind that listens.]</p>
<p>Nyx: Yes.</p>
<p>Nyx: Here, we do it before.</p>
<p>Nyx: That is the difference between extraction and care.</p>
<p>[Avyanna swallows.]</p>
<p>Elisira: Avyanna.</p>
<p>[Avyanna&#x27;s spine goes rigid.]</p>
<p>Elisira: What did you learn.</p>
<p>[Not &quot;what did you do wrong.&quot;]</p>
<p>[What did you learn.]</p>
<p>Avyanna: [working] That reporting a problem isn&#x27;t... confessing guilt.</p>
<p>Elisira: Correct.</p>
<p>Avyanna: That tools aren&#x27;t personal property.</p>
<p>[Bubbles&#x27; fans shift, pleased.]</p>
<p>Avyanna: That &quot;extra&quot; versus &quot;spare&quot; matters.</p>
<p>Elia: [delighted] Yes. Vocabulary war.</p>
<p>Vesper isn&#x27;t here.</p>
<p>[And yet Avyanna hears her anyway: words are leverage.]</p>
<p>Rho: Also learned the bridge conduit was cooked.</p>
<p>Jalen: [over comm, dry] It is not cooked. It is lightly toasted.</p>
<p>Elia: Toasted is still edible. Therefore safe.</p>
<p>Jalen: [flat] That is not how ships work.</p>
<p>&lt;WAFFLE.BAT// COMMENTARY: toasted ship is funny concept&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;CINNAMON.EXE// CORRECTION: toasted ship is unacceptable&gt;</p>
<hr>
<p>[Elisira stamps the slate with a final note.]</p>
<p>Elisira: No blame assigned.</p>
<p>[Avyanna&#x27;s chest tightens.]</p>
<p>Avyanna: That&#x27;s... written down too.</p>
<p>Elisira: Yes.</p>
<p>Elisira: Because we mean it.</p>
<p>[Avyanna nods once, hard.]</p>
<p>(Say what you mean. Mean what you say.)</p>
<p>[The phrase is becoming a rail inside her.]</p>
<p>[Elia stands, stretches, and claps Avyanna on the shoulder-not hard, not claiming. Just present.]</p>
<p>Elia: You did good, Avy.</p>
<p>Avyanna: [quiet] That&#x27;s not a metric.</p>
<p>Elia: [grinning] It is my metric.</p>
<p>[Avyanna can&#x27;t help it.]</p>
<p>[She laughs.]</p>
</div>

