:: Act1 16d Convoy Transit Comparison
<h1>Optional 16d: Convoy Transit Comparison</h1>
<p class="source-note">Source: 16d_convoy_transit_comparison.md</p>
<div class="scene-prose">
<p>&gt; **LUMEN THIEF - TRANSIT NOTE (INTERNAL):** &gt; *Topic: myth is procedure other people can&#x27;t afford* &gt; *Reminder: calm is a capability*</p>
<hr>
<p>[They fall in with a convoy because the corridor is shifting and sometimes &quot;normal&quot; is safer than &quot;alone.&quot;]</p>
<p>[Two ships ahead. One behind.]</p>
<p>[A fourth off their port side, pacing them like it wants to be seen as equal.]</p>
<p>[Its lights are brighter than necessary.]</p>
<p>[Its comms are louder than necessary.]</p>
<p>[Its transponder says insured. The kind of insured that makes people assume the universe will apologize if it hurts you.]</p>
<hr>
<p>[The Lumen Thief bridge is in working-quiet.]</p>
<p>[Jalen in the pilot cradle. Elisira standing behind them with a slate. Rho in the doorway with coffee that smells like stubbornness. Vesper at the rail with a datapad full of jurisdiction traps. Elia pretending to be bored near weapons control.]</p>
<p>[Avyanna at the last open station, strapped in, pretending her ribs aren&#x27;t humming with the corridor&#x27;s wrongness.]</p>
<p>(Convoy means witnesses. Witnesses mean lists.)</p>
<p>&lt;CINNAMON.EXE// OBSERVATION: convoy formation recognized | NOTE: increased traffic reduces ambiguity but increases attention | INFERENCE: risk trade | CONFIDENCE: 0.78&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;BUBBLES// REMINDER: do not interpret convoy proximity as safety&gt;</p>
<p>Elia: [cheerful] Thank you, Bubbles. Very comforting.</p>
<p>Bubbles: [over speaker, earnest] You are welcome.</p>
<hr>
<p>[The insured ship pings them.]</p>
<p>[A hail request slides onto the console with the casual entitlement of something used to being answered.]</p>
<p>Jalen: [flat] Decline.</p>
<p>Vesper: [without looking up] Let them talk at us for a second. It will cost less than them inventing a story about why we refused.</p>
<p>[Jalen makes a sound that is not agreement and taps accept anyway.]</p>
<hr>
<p>Other Captain: [voice smooth, broadcast-quality] Independent vessel Lumen Thief, this is convoy lead for insured hauler group. We see you&#x27;re running the same lane. Confirm you can maintain pace and formation.</p>
<p>[There&#x27;s a pause where the captain expects deference.]</p>
<p>[Avyanna knows the shape of that pause. The mine was built out of it.]</p>
<p>Vesper: [mild] Define &quot;confirm.&quot;</p>
<p>Other Captain: [a beat] Acknowledge that you won&#x27;t become a hazard.</p>
<p>Vesper: We are not a hazard.</p>
<p>Other Captain: [tiny laugh] Everyone says that.</p>
<p>Elisira: Everyone lies.</p>
<hr>
<p>Other Captain: We&#x27;ve got ten onboard. Standard redundancy. We can provide assistance if your systems lag.</p>
<p>[Ten onboard.]</p>
<p>[Avyanna pictures it: a medic that isn&#x27;t also a negotiator; a pilot that isn&#x27;t also a lawyer; a tech that isn&#x27;t also a fighter.]</p>
<p>[Ten people to do what this ship does with fewer bodies and more voices.]</p>
<p>(Unfair.)</p>
<p>Rho: [to no one in particular] We don&#x27;t need help.</p>
<p>Other Captain: [polite] It&#x27;s not charity. It&#x27;s protocol.</p>
<p>Vesper: Protocol is enforcement with manners.</p>
<p>Other Captain: ...Excuse me?</p>
<p>Vesper: Nothing. Continue your checklists.</p>
<hr>
<p>[The corridor shifts.]</p>
<p>[Not dramatic. Not a scream.]</p>
<p>[Just a pressure change that makes Avyanna&#x27;s teeth ache and her hands want to clench.]</p>
<p>(Mine collapse.)</p>
<p>Elia: [bright] Ooh. That&#x27;s a seam.</p>
<p>Jalen: [quiet] Drift left two degrees. Hold. Hold.</p>
<p>[The Lumen Thief slides like it enjoys obeying someone who knows why they&#x27;re asking.]</p>
<p>&lt;CINNAMON.EXE// OBSERVATION: shear gradient increasing | ACTION: reduce nonessential power draw 9% | INFERENCE: lower thermal noise signature | CONFIDENCE: 0.82&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;WAFFLE.BAT// COMMENTARY: corridor thinks it&#x27;s funny&gt;</p>
<p>[Avyanna swallows.]</p>
<p>[She tracks Vesper&#x27;s hands. The way they stay on the rail. The way her posture stays open even when everything in the universe is trying to make her shrink.]</p>
<p>(This is what control looks like. Not yelling. Not threats. Just choices held steady.)</p>
<hr>
<p>Other Captain: [voice tightening] Convoy, confirm stability. Readouts just spiked.</p>
<p>[Over comm, the other ship&#x27;s bridge goes from smooth to crowded.]</p>
<p>Other Crew Voice: (pilot) Lane&#x27;s drifting, Captain.</p>
<p>Other Crew Voice: (tech) Guidance is lagging.</p>
<p>Other Crew Voice: (medic) Strap in, strap in, strap in-</p>
<p>Other Crew Voice: (admin) Insurance guidance says reduce speed twelve percent.</p>
<p>Other Crew Voice: (someone else) That&#x27;s going to break formation.</p>
<p>Other Captain: Hold formation. Maintain pace. We&#x27;re insured for this corridor rating.</p>
<p>[Avyanna feels her stomach twist.]</p>
<p>(Insured doesn&#x27;t mean safe. Insured means someone decided what your death is worth.)</p>
<hr>
<p>[The convoy ship beside them shudders.]</p>
<p>[Its running lights flicker once.]</p>
<p>[Avyanna hears a thin, ugly sound through the hull: metal complaining.]</p>
<p>Jalen: [calm] They&#x27;re going to overcorrect.</p>
<p>Elisira: [already moving on her slate] Their captain is forcing pride into physics.</p>
<p>Elia: [still cheerful, but the cheer has teeth] Do we rescue them or let them learn.</p>
<p>Vesper: We do not let ten people die to teach a lesson.</p>
<p>Rho: [grim] We also don&#x27;t let them drag us into their panic.</p>
<hr>
<p>[Avyanna watches Vesper&#x27;s profile.]</p>
<p>[The way she holds both truths without flinching.]</p>
<p>(Floors, not thrones. Floors still have edges.)</p>
<p>Vesper: [into comm, precise] Convoy lead. Your readouts are lying to you.</p>
<p>Other Captain: [sharp] Say again?</p>
<p>Vesper: Your insurer&#x27;s guidance is a generic template. This corridor is shifting faster than their update cycle.</p>
<p>Other Captain: And you know that how?</p>
<p>[The question is bait.]</p>
<p>[Prove yourself for free. Show your hand. Earn their belief.]</p>
<p>[Avyanna feels Elia watching her. Waiting to see what she does with a pause shaped like hierarchy.]</p>
<p>Avyanna: [quiet, into her mic] Because you just said &quot;reduce speed twelve percent&quot; like a prayer.</p>
<p>[Silence.]</p>
<p>Vesper&#x27;s head turns slightly. Not surprise. Acknowledgment.</p>
<p>Avyanna: That&#x27;s not a measurement. It&#x27;s a slogan.</p>
<p>Other Captain: [too controlled] Watch your tone, kid.</p>
<p>Elisira: [flat] Define &quot;kid.&quot;</p>
<hr>
<p>Vesper: [still calm] If you want to stay in formation, you need to drift left by two degrees and stop fighting the seam.</p>
<p>Other Captain: That&#x27;s not in our- our procedures.</p>
<p>Vesper: Your procedures were written for paperwork, not weather.</p>
<p>Other Captain: [breathing audible now] We are insured-</p>
<p>Rho: [cuts in, voice like a clamp] Insurance doesn&#x27;t fly your ship.</p>
<hr>
<p>[The convoy lead hesitates.]</p>
<p>[Avyanna can hear ten people&#x27;s fear stacking behind one person&#x27;s pride.]</p>
<p>Other Crew Voice: (pilot, urgent) Captain, if we don&#x27;t adjust we&#x27;re going to shear.</p>
<p>Other Captain: ...Drift left two degrees. Hold.</p>
<p>[The other ship slides.]</p>
<p>[Not as clean as the Lumen Thief.]</p>
<p>[But it slides.]</p>
<p>[The metal-complaint sound eases by a fraction.]</p>
<hr>
<p>Other Captain: [after a long breath] Acknowledged.</p>
<p>Other Captain: ...Thank you.</p>
<p>Vesper: [immediate] You&#x27;re welcome.</p>
<p>[Avyanna feels something in her chest loosen.]</p>
<p>(No punishment. No invoice. Just a fix, and then you move on.)</p>
<hr>
<p>[The convoy keeps moving.]</p>
<p>[The insured ship doesn&#x27;t try to pace them anymore.]</p>
<p>[It drops half a length back, like it suddenly remembers distance is etiquette.]</p>
<p>[Before they cut comms, the other captain speaks again.]</p>
<p>Other Captain: Lumen Thief-</p>
<p>[Not bait this time.]</p>
<p>[Not posturing.]</p>
<p>Other Captain: Are you always like this.</p>
<p>Elia: [bright] Like what.</p>
<p>Other Captain: Like you already know what the corridor is going to do.</p>
<p>Jalen: [flat] No.</p>
<p>Jalen: We just listen faster.</p>
<p>Elisira: And we don&#x27;t worship templates.</p>
<p>Vesper: And we ask &quot;who enforces it&quot; before we trust it.</p>
<p>Rho: And we don&#x27;t confuse insured with immortal.</p>
<p>[A pause.]</p>
<p>Other Captain: ...Copy.</p>
<p>[The channel closes.]</p>
<hr>
<p>[For a while, nobody on the bridge speaks.]</p>
<p>[Avyanna watches the stars smear and un-smear.]</p>
<p>[Watches the convoy hold itself together on a borrowed lesson.]</p>
<p>(They&#x27;ll tell people.)</p>
<p>(Not &quot;we survived.&quot; They&#x27;ll tell people about the ship that corrected an insured captain mid-seam without raising its voice.)</p>
<p>&lt;CINNAMON.EXE// OBSERVATION: external comms silence persists | INFERENCE: rumor retention likelihood high | CONFIDENCE: 0.77&gt;</p>
<p>Elia: [soft, satisfied] See.</p>
<p>Avyanna: What.</p>
<p>Elia: Myths are just other people&#x27;s fear, organized.</p>
<p>Elia: The trick is making them afraid of the right thing.</p>
<p>[Vesper doesn&#x27;t look away from her screen.]</p>
<p>Vesper: The right thing is the system.</p>
<p>[Avyanna nods.]</p>
<p>[Her hands unclench.]</p>
<p>[Outside, the corridor keeps pretending it&#x27;s weather.]</p>
</div>

