:: Act1 16e Senna Math Is Power
<h1>Optional 16e: Senna Math Is Power</h1>
<p class="source-note">Source: 16e_senna_math_is_power.md</p>
<div class="scene-prose">
<p>&gt; **[INTERSTITIAL - OCCURS POST-CH16]** &gt; *Trigger: numbers as a weapon against contracts* &gt; *Purpose: Senna&#x27;s version of &quot;show me the math&quot;*</p>
<hr>
<p>[Rho and Cinnamon taught her compound interest like it was a knife safety lesson.]</p>
<p>[Not scary.]</p>
<p>[Necessary.]</p>
<p>[Avyanna walked away from the galley with her head full of percentages that felt like teeth.]</p>
<p>[Now she lies awake, staring at the ceiling, repeating numbers like prayers she doesn&#x27;t believe in.]</p>
<p>Twenty-two percent annual.</p>
<p>Monthly compounding.</p>
<p>Hidden fees that aren&#x27;t hidden if you know where to look.</p>
<p>(If they won&#x27;t show you the math, they&#x27;re lying.)</p>
<p>[The sentence is Rho&#x27;s.]</p>
<p>[But it scrapes at something older in her memory.]</p>
<hr>
<p>## Intercut - AE Site K-9 (Senna&#x27;s Ledger)</p>
<p>[Senna doesn&#x27;t have a datapad.]</p>
<p>[Datapads belong to supervisors.]</p>
<p>[Senna has a strip of packing paper stolen from the supply bay and a chunk of charcoal.]</p>
<p>[Avyanna sits beside her in the shadow of a support column, knees tucked to her chest.]</p>
<p>Avyanna: Why are we doing this.</p>
<p>Senna: Because you&#x27;re curious.</p>
<p>Avyanna: Curiosity gets people hurt.</p>
<p>Senna: Curiosity gets people out.</p>
<p>[Senna draws a line, then another, making a crude table.]</p>
<p>Senna: Here is what they tell you.</p>
<p>[She writes:]</p>
<p>QUOTA: 100</p>
<p>PAY: 0</p>
<p>[Avyanna snorts quietly.]</p>
<p>Avyanna: That&#x27;s not math.</p>
<p>Senna: It is.</p>
<p>Senna: It&#x27;s just a lie-shaped one.</p>
<p>[Senna writes below it:]</p>
<p>PENALTY: -5</p>
<p>PENALTY: -5</p>
<p>PENALTY: -5</p>
<p>[Avyanna watches the list grow.]</p>
<p>Avyanna: That&#x27;s what they do.</p>
<p>Senna: Yes.</p>
<p>Senna: Now watch the trick.</p>
<p>[Senna circles the penalties.]</p>
<p>Senna: They call it &quot;compliance.&quot;</p>
<p>Senna: They call it &quot;training.&quot;</p>
<p>Senna: But it&#x27;s interest.</p>
<p>[Avyanna frowns.]</p>
<p>Avyanna: We don&#x27;t get paid.</p>
<p>Senna: You get charged.</p>
<p>Senna: Debt doesn&#x27;t care if you ever saw money.</p>
<p>[Senna draws an arrow.]</p>
<p>Senna: If you owe five today, you owe seven tomorrow.</p>
<p>Avyanna: Why.</p>
<p>Senna: Because the number is a weapon.</p>
<p>Senna: The weapon works best when you don&#x27;t understand it.</p>
<hr>
<p>[Avyanna&#x27;s throat tightens.]</p>
<p>Avyanna: I can&#x27;t do that math.</p>
<p>Senna: You can.</p>
<p>[Senna taps the paper.]</p>
<p>Senna: Shortcut.</p>
<p>Senna: If they refuse to show you how the number changes, assume it changes against you.</p>
<p>Senna: If they show you a number once and never again, assume it&#x27;s moving.</p>
<p>Senna: If they tell you &quot;it&#x27;s standard,&quot; assume &quot;standard&quot; means &quot;profitable.&quot;</p>
<p>[Avyanna stares.]</p>
<p>Avyanna: That&#x27;s... not math.</p>
<p>Senna: It&#x27;s survival.</p>
<p>[Senna leans in.]</p>
<p>Senna: Real math comes later.</p>
<p>Senna: First you learn the rule.</p>
<p>Senna: If they won&#x27;t show you the math, they&#x27;re lying.</p>
<p>[Avyanna swallows the sentence like it&#x27;s contraband food.]</p>
<hr>
<p>## Return - Ship Ceiling</p>
<p>[Avyanna&#x27;s eyes snap open.]</p>
<p>[The ceiling is clean.]</p>
<p>[The air doesn&#x27;t taste like metal.]</p>
<p>[But the sentence is still there, bright and sharp as a tool.]</p>
<p>(If they won&#x27;t show you the math, they&#x27;re lying.)</p>
<p>[She sits up.]</p>
<p>[Finds the notebook from Senna&#x27;s &quot;small good thing&quot; rule.]</p>
<p>[On the next page, she writes:]</p>
<p>If they won&#x27;t show you the math, they&#x27;re lying.</p>
<p>[Under it, smaller:]</p>
<p>Ask where the number comes from.</p>
<p>Ask who benefits when it changes.</p>
<p>[Avyanna closes the notebook and rests her forehead against it.]</p>
<p>[She doesn&#x27;t feel smart.]</p>
<p>[She feels armed.]</p>
<hr>
<p>*End Chapter 16e*</p>
</div>

