:: Act1 17d Library Glossary Of Lies
<h1>Optional 17d: Library Glossary Of Lies</h1>
<p class="source-note">Source: 17d_library_glossary_of_lies.md</p>
<div class="scene-prose">
<p>&gt; **[SCENE - OCCURS POST-CH17c, SELF-DIRECTED STUDY]** &gt; *Location: Library / Study alcove* &gt; *Present: Avyanna; brief check-ins from Vesper and Cinnamon.exe* &gt; *Teaching: reader/world literacy via Avyanna&#x27;s notes; &quot;describe, then interrogate&quot; as reflex*</p>
<hr>
<p>[The library is small, which makes it feel safer.]</p>
<p>[Shelves. Terminals. A table with a lamp that throws warm light without being asked.]</p>
<p>[A stamp on the wall reads:]</p>
<p>&gt; **TAKE WHAT YOU NEED**</p>
<p>[Avyanna reads it like it&#x27;s a threat.]</p>
<p>(Need according to who. Enforced by whom. Paid how.)</p>
<p>[No one jumps out to correct her for touching a book.]</p>
<p>[She touches one anyway.]</p>
<p>[The cover is worn. The title is boring: *Civic Forms and Jurisdictional Practice (Guild Primer).*]</p>
<p>[She sits.]</p>
<p>[She opens her notebook.]</p>
<p>[On the first page she writes, in careful block letters:]</p>
<p>&gt; **GLOSSARY OF LIES**</p>
<p>[Then, underneath, columns:]</p>
<p>&gt; WORD &gt; &gt; WHAT THEY SAY IT MEANS &gt; &gt; WHO PROFITS &gt; &gt; WHO ENFORCES &gt; &gt; WHAT IT COSTS</p>
<p>(If I can name the shape of the trap, maybe it stops being invisible.)</p>
<hr>
<p>[She starts with the words that keep showing up like insects in her teeth.]</p>
<p>**COMPLIANCE**</p>
<p>[She pauses.]</p>
<p>[In the mine, &quot;compliance&quot; meant: do what you&#x27;re told or your body becomes a lesson.]</p>
<p>[She writes:]</p>
<p>&gt; WHAT THEY SAY: safety / order / protocol &gt; &gt; WHO PROFITS: whoever issues the rule &gt; &gt; WHO ENFORCES: guards / forms / hunger &gt; &gt; COST: agency</p>
<p>[The word sits there, ugly and honest.]</p>
<p>[She turns the page.]</p>
<p>**WEATHER**</p>
<p>[She almost laughs.]</p>
<p>(Weather. Like the corridor is a sky and not a mechanism.)</p>
<p>&gt; WHAT THEY SAY: natural / inevitable / no one&#x27;s fault &gt; &gt; WHO PROFITS: insurance / people selling &quot;protection&quot; &gt; &gt; WHO ENFORCES: fear / delayed shipments / fees &gt; &gt; COST: questions</p>
<p>[She taps her pen.]</p>
<p>[Elia would write: &quot;STAB IT.&quot;]</p>
<p>[Elisira would write: &quot;FILE IT.&quot;]</p>
<p>[Vesper would write: &quot;PROVE IT.&quot;]</p>
<p>[Avyanna writes:]</p>
<p>&gt; NEXT: find pattern that shows it isn&#x27;t weather</p>
<p>[It feels like building a knife one note at a time.]</p>
<hr>
<p>[Cinnamon pings the terminal with a small notification.]</p>
<p>&lt;CINNAMON.EXE// NOTE: good structure | SUGGESTION: add &quot;what would disprove it&quot; column&gt;</p>
<p>[Avyanna stares at that.]</p>
<p>Avyanna: [muttering] Of course you want a disproof column.</p>
<p>&lt;CINNAMON.EXE// AFFIRMATION: yes | COMMENTARY: adversaries exist&gt;</p>
<p>[She adds a sixth column.]</p>
<p>&gt; WHAT WOULD PROVE ME WRONG</p>
<p>[The notebook looks more dangerous immediately.]</p>
<hr>
<p>[She keeps going.]</p>
<p>**VOLUNTARY DISCLOSURE**</p>
<p>&gt; WHAT THEY SAY: transparency / cooperation &gt; &gt; WHO PROFITS: whoever wants your history &gt; &gt; WHO ENFORCES: social pressure / clerks with smiles &gt; &gt; COST: leverage (yours) &gt; &gt; DISPROOF: they cite a law with enforcement and consequence</p>
<p>[She underlines &quot;cite a law.&quot;]</p>
<p>**PROCESSING FEE**</p>
<p>[Her pen hovers.]</p>
<p>(Mine word. Station word. Same shape.)</p>
<p>&gt; WHAT THEY SAY: administrative necessity &gt; &gt; WHO PROFITS: middlemen &gt; &gt; WHO ENFORCES: delays / &quot;lost paperwork&quot; &gt; &gt; COST: time / dignity &gt; &gt; DISPROOF: fee correlates to actual labor</p>
<hr>
<p>[A shadow falls over her page.]</p>
<p>[Vesper stands at the end of the table with a mug in hand, reading without touching.]</p>
<p>Vesper: Glossary of lies.</p>
<p>Avyanna: [bracing] It&#x27;s... for me.</p>
<p>Vesper: Good.</p>
<p>[Avyanna blinks.]</p>
<p>Avyanna: Good?</p>
<p>Vesper: Yes.</p>
<p>Vesper: This is how you stop being controlled by vocabulary.</p>
<p>[Vesper&#x27;s gaze moves to the disproof column.]</p>
<p>Vesper: You added falsification tests.</p>
<p>Avyanna: Cinnamon told me to.</p>
<p>Vesper: [dry] Cinnamon is correct.</p>
<p>[Vesper taps the edge of the spreadsheet.]</p>
<p>Vesper: Add one more column.</p>
<p>Avyanna: Of course.</p>
<p>Vesper: &quot;How would I explain this to someone else.&quot;</p>
<p>Avyanna: Why.</p>
<p>Vesper: Because if you can teach it, you own it.</p>
<p>[Avyanna&#x27;s throat tightens.]</p>
<p>(Own it. Not be owned by it.)</p>
<p>Avyanna: Okay.</p>
<p>[She writes:]</p>
<p>&gt; HOW TO TEACH IT</p>
<hr>
<p>[Vesper sets the mug down beside her notebook.]</p>
<p>[Not a gift. Not a transaction. Just a fact: warm liquid exists, and you are allowed to drink it.]</p>
<p>Vesper: Keep going.</p>
<p>[Then she leaves.]</p>
<p>[Avyanna watches her go and feels, for a moment, like she is being trained to survive a world that wants her illiterate.]</p>
<p>[She looks back down at her notebook.]</p>
<p>[She writes a new entry.]</p>
<p>**FAMILY**</p>
<p>[Her hand pauses.]</p>
<p>(Not established. Not defined. Not safe. Not a trap. Maybe.)</p>
<p>[She writes in the first column anyway.]</p>
<p>&gt; WHAT THEY SAY: nothing</p>
<p>[She exhales.]</p>
<p>[Then, carefully:]</p>
<p>&gt; WHO ENFORCES: us</p>
<hr>
<p>[She adds more entries until her hand cramps.]</p>
<p>**JURISDICTION**</p>
<p>&gt; WHAT THEY SAY: neutral authority / procedure &gt; &gt; WHO PROFITS: whoever owns the court &gt; &gt; WHO ENFORCES: uniforms / locks / paperwork &gt; &gt; COST: options &gt; &gt; DISPROOF: enforcement is absent</p>
<p>**HUMANITARIAN**</p>
<p>[She stares at the word for a long time.]</p>
<p>(Humanitarian is what people call themselves when they want to feel clean.)</p>
<p>&gt; WHAT THEY SAY: mercy &gt; &gt; WHO PROFITS: whoever controls the aid &gt; &gt; WHO ENFORCES: distribution offices / &quot;eligibility&quot; &gt; &gt; COST: dignity (if conditional) &gt; &gt; DISPROOF: aid is delivered without leverage</p>
<p>**SAFETY**</p>
<p>&gt; WHAT THEY SAY: protection &gt; &gt; WHO PROFITS: whoever sells it &gt; &gt; WHO ENFORCES: fear &gt; &gt; COST: freedom &gt; &gt; DISPROOF: safety increases options instead of reducing them</p>
<p>[The last one makes her pause.]</p>
<p>(Safety that cages you is not safety.)</p>
<hr>
<p>[A new book appears on the table beside her notebook.]</p>
<p>[She didn&#x27;t hear the door.]</p>
<p>[Bubbles must have done it. Or Elisira. Or the ship itself, quietly feeding her curiosity.]</p>
<p>[*Rim Accord Civic Practices: A Field Guide.*]</p>
<p>[A sticky note is attached to the cover in neat handwriting.]</p>
<p>&gt; **This one will help you avoid talking yourself into a trap. - E**</p>
<p>[E.]</p>
<p>[Elisira.]</p>
<p>[Avyanna touches the note like it might burn.]</p>
<p>(She&#x27;s paying attention.)</p>
<p>[Avyanna opens the book.]</p>
<p>[It is full of arguments.]</p>
<p>[Not propaganda arguments. Real arguments: people disagreeing on paper because disagreement is allowed to exist in public.]</p>
<p>[Her stomach twists with something that isn&#x27;t fear.]</p>
<p>(Noise. Choice. Floors.)</p>
<hr>
<p>[Cinnamon pings again.]</p>
<p>&lt;CINNAMON.EXE// QUESTION: do you want this indexed&gt;</p>
<p>Avyanna: Indexed.</p>
<p>&lt;CINNAMON.EXE// CLARIFICATION: do you want privacy on your notes&gt;</p>
<p>[Avyanna&#x27;s heart stutters.]</p>
<p>Avyanna: Privacy.</p>
<p>&lt;CINNAMON.EXE// RESPONSE: default privacy enabled | NOTE: sharing is always opt-in&gt;</p>
<p>[Avyanna&#x27;s eyes sting. Again. Annoying. Habit-forming.]</p>
<hr>
<p>[She writes one more entry, smaller than the others.]</p>
<p>**OPTIONAL**</p>
<p>&gt; WHAT THEY SAY: choice &gt; &gt; WHO PROFITS: depends &gt; &gt; WHO ENFORCES: no one &gt; &gt; COST: fear (yours) &gt; &gt; DISPROOF: nothing happens when you decline</p>
<p>[She underlines the last line three times.]</p>
<p>[Then she closes her notebook.]</p>
<p>[She sits in the library until her body stops expecting someone to come take the table away.]</p>
</div>

