:: Act1 17e Nyx And Halcyon Ward Lesson
<h1>Optional 17e: Nyx And Halcyon Ward Lesson</h1>
<p class="source-note">Source: 17e_nyx_and_halcyon_ward_lesson.md</p>
<div class="scene-prose">
<p>&gt; **[INTERSTITIAL - OCCURS POST-CH17]** &gt; *Trigger: Nyx says &quot;witness&quot; like it&#x27;s a verb* &gt; *Purpose: show Sutured practice as discipline, not myth*</p>
<hr>
<p>[Nyx&#x27;s lessons are quiet in the way a blade is quiet.]</p>
<p>[Avyanna finds them in a corner of the ship that smells faintly of herbs and ozone, surrounded by small ward-stones laid out like a careful argument.]</p>
<p>Nyx: Sit.</p>
<p>[Avyanna sits.]</p>
<p>Nyx: Breathe.</p>
<p>[Avyanna breathes.]</p>
<p>Nyx: Now witness.</p>
<p>Avyanna: [frowning] Witness what.</p>
<p>Nyx: Your body.</p>
<p>Nyx: Your fear.</p>
<p>Nyx: The story you keep telling yourself about what fear means.</p>
<p>[Avyanna&#x27;s jaw tightens.]</p>
<p>Avyanna: Fear means I&#x27;m about to get punished.</p>
<p>Nyx: [calm] That is one story.</p>
<p>Nyx: Not the only one.</p>
<p>[Nyx&#x27;s fingers trace the edge of a ward-stone.]</p>
<p>[Avyanna watches their hands.]</p>
<p>[They move like someone taught them how to touch danger without flinching.]</p>
<hr>
<p>## Intercut - Halcyon Vess (Ward-Keeping)</p>
<p>[The room is bright, but not warm.]</p>
<p>[Stone walls. Clean floors. A training space that pretends it&#x27;s neutral.]</p>
<p>[Nyx is younger here-still a student, still sharp-edged in the way people are when they haven&#x27;t learned what softness costs.]</p>
<p>[Across from them, Halcyon stands with a ward-bundle in their hands.]</p>
<p>[Halcyon&#x27;s hair is tied back. Their sleeves are rolled to the elbow. Their eyes are steady.]</p>
<p>Halcyon: Again.</p>
<p>[Nyx redraws the ward circle with chalk.]</p>
<p>[The line wobbles.]</p>
<p>Halcyon: Stop.</p>
<p>[Nyx freezes.]</p>
<p>Halcyon: Witness the wobble.</p>
<p>Nyx: I saw it.</p>
<p>Halcyon: You noticed it.</p>
<p>Halcyon: That&#x27;s not the same.</p>
<p>[Nyx&#x27;s jaw clenches.]</p>
<p>Nyx: It&#x27;s chalk. It doesn&#x27;t matter.</p>
<p>Halcyon: It matters because you decided it doesn&#x27;t.</p>
<p>Halcyon: That decision is how people die in corridors.</p>
<p>[Nyx swallows.]</p>
<p>Halcyon: You don&#x27;t get to be vague.</p>
<p>Halcyon: Witness is precision.</p>
<hr>
<p>[Halcyon kneels beside the chalk line without crossing it.]</p>
<p>[They don&#x27;t fix it for Nyx.]</p>
<p>[They point.]</p>
<p>Halcyon: Where did you exhale.</p>
<p>Nyx: [confused] Here.</p>
<p>Halcyon: Your breath moved your hand.</p>
<p>Nyx: That&#x27;s ridiculous.</p>
<p>Halcyon: It&#x27;s physics.</p>
<p>Halcyon: Physics doesn&#x27;t care if you respect it.</p>
<p>[Nyx&#x27;s mouth tightens.]</p>
<p>Nyx: What do you want me to do.</p>
<p>Halcyon: Say it out loud.</p>
<p>Halcyon: &quot;My breath moved my hand.&quot;</p>
<p>[Nyx glares.]</p>
<p>Halcyon: No penalty for honesty.</p>
<p>[Nyx&#x27;s throat works.]</p>
<p>Nyx: My breath moved my hand.</p>
<p>[Halcyon nods.]</p>
<p>Halcyon: Good.</p>
<p>Halcyon: Now you can correct it.</p>
<hr>
<p>[Nyx redraws the circle.]</p>
<p>[This time, they breathe differently.]</p>
<p>[The line holds.]</p>
<p>[The ward-stone hums faintly.]</p>
<p>Halcyon: Witness.</p>
<p>Nyx: The line is stable.</p>
<p>Halcyon: The line is stable because you were willing to see what caused it to fail.</p>
<p>Halcyon: That is the whole job.</p>
<p>[Nyx looks up.]</p>
<p>Nyx: And if someone is bleeding and the ward fails anyway.</p>
<p>Halcyon: Then you witness that too.</p>
<p>Halcyon: And you don&#x27;t lie about what you could have done.</p>
<p>Halcyon: And you don&#x27;t pretend your shame is the same thing as responsibility.</p>
<p>[Nyx&#x27;s eyes sting.]</p>
<p>Nyx: That sounds cruel.</p>
<p>Halcyon: It&#x27;s mercy.</p>
<p>Halcyon: To the truth.</p>
<hr>
<p>## Return - Ship Corner</p>
<p>[Nyx&#x27;s fingers stop moving.]</p>
<p>Nyx: Witness is not prayer.</p>
<p>Nyx: It&#x27;s method.</p>
<p>[Avyanna swallows.]</p>
<p>Avyanna: Method for what.</p>
<p>Nyx: For not becoming a liar when you&#x27;re scared.</p>
<p>[A beat.]</p>
<p>Nyx: For not turning other people into acceptable losses to protect your own story.</p>
<p>[Avyanna&#x27;s chest tightens.]</p>
<p>Avyanna: Okay.</p>
<p>Nyx: Good.</p>
<p>Nyx: Again.</p>
<p>[Nyx pushes a ward-stone toward her.]</p>
<p>[Avyanna picks it up like it might bite.]</p>
<p>[It doesn&#x27;t.]</p>
<p>[It just sits in her hand, heavy, waiting to be witnessed honestly.]</p>
<hr>
<p>*End Chapter 17e*</p>
</div>

