:: Act1 19c Receipt Practice
<h1>Optional 19c: Receipt Practice</h1>
<p class="source-note">Source: 19c_receipt_practice.md</p>
<div class="scene-prose">
<p>&gt; **[SCENE - OCCURS BETWEEN CH19 AND CH20, PRE-HEARING WORK]** &gt; *Location: Vesper&#x27;s office* &gt; *Present: Avyanna, Vesper* &gt; *Teaching: &quot;claim -&gt; evidence -&gt; inference&quot; as a safe spine; trauma handled as procedure*</p>
<hr>
<p>[Vesper&#x27;s office is too orderly to be natural.]</p>
<p>[Shelves. Binders. A desk that looks like it has never been used for anything except war.]</p>
<p>[Avyanna sits across from Vesper with a stack of printouts and a pen that feels heavier than it should.]</p>
<p>Vesper: Tell me what you saw.</p>
<p>[Avyanna&#x27;s jaw tightens on instinct.]</p>
<p>(If I tell the truth wrong, it becomes a weapon aimed at me.)</p>
<p>Avyanna: Which part.</p>
<p>Vesper: The part you are scared to put into words.</p>
<p>[Avyanna swallows.]</p>
<p>Avyanna: The station clerk tried to make me sign &quot;voluntary disclosure.&quot;</p>
<p>Vesper: Good. That&#x27;s a claim.</p>
<p>Avyanna: [baffled] That&#x27;s not-</p>
<p>Vesper: It is. &quot;Clerk attempted coercion.&quot; Claim.</p>
<p>[Vesper taps the printouts.]</p>
<p>Vesper: Evidence.</p>
<p>Avyanna: The slip. The camera footage request Elisira filed. The time stamp on the terminal log.</p>
<p>Vesper: Good.</p>
<p>Vesper: Inference.</p>
<p>Avyanna: They were fishing. For identity. For contacts.</p>
<p>Vesper: Next step.</p>
<p>Avyanna: Report it. Archive it. Don&#x27;t sign.</p>
<p>[Vesper&#x27;s mouth twitches.]</p>
<p>Vesper: You&#x27;re learning.</p>
<p>[Avyanna&#x27;s chest tightens.]</p>
<p>Avyanna: I&#x27;m trying.</p>
<p>Vesper: Trying is a verb. Keep using it.</p>
<hr>
<p>[Vesper slides a new printout toward her.]</p>
<p>[Aurum-coded header. Not the mine&#x27;s logo, exactly-cleaner, but the same colors.]</p>
<p>[Avyanna&#x27;s vision tunnels.]</p>
<p>[The room tilts.]</p>
<p>(No.)</p>
<p>[Her hands go cold.]</p>
<p>Vesper: Avyanna. Eyes on me.</p>
<p>[Avyanna forces her gaze up.]</p>
<p>Avyanna: [thin] That looks like-</p>
<p>Vesper: Aurum.</p>
<p>Avyanna: [breathing wrong] They&#x27;re here.</p>
<p>Vesper: No.</p>
<p>Vesper: Not physically.</p>
<p>Vesper: It&#x27;s a record artifact. A data style. A mimic.</p>
<p>[Vesper&#x27;s voice stays calm on purpose.]</p>
<p>Vesper: Check.</p>
<p>Avyanna: [after a beat] Yellow.</p>
<p>Vesper: Good. Stay with yellow.</p>
<p>[Vesper does not touch her.]</p>
<p>[She doesn&#x27;t have to.]</p>
<p>[She moves the printout away, flips it face-down.]</p>
<p>Vesper: We don&#x27;t process trauma by pretending it isn&#x27;t there.</p>
<p>Vesper: We process it by turning it into something that can be handled.</p>
<p>Avyanna: That sounds like you.</p>
<p>Vesper: It is me.</p>
<hr>
<p>[Vesper opens a binder and pulls out a template.]</p>
<p>&gt; **WITNESS STATEMENT (DRAFT)** &gt; &gt; *Claim* &gt; &gt; *Evidence* &gt; &gt; *Inference* &gt; &gt; *Confounders* &gt; &gt; *What would prove me wrong*</p>
<p>Avyanna: Cinnamon would like that.</p>
<p>Vesper: Cinnamon does like that.</p>
<p>Vesper: Now.</p>
<p>Vesper: We&#x27;re going to practice on something that won&#x27;t kill you if you get it wrong.</p>
<p>Avyanna: [dry] That&#x27;s generous.</p>
<p>Vesper: It&#x27;s responsible.</p>
<p>[Avyanna picks up her pen.]</p>
<p>[Her hand still shakes, but she can write through it.]</p>
<p>Avyanna: Claim: the mine&#x27;s medical bay neglected workers on purpose.</p>
<p>Vesper: Evidence.</p>
<p>[Avyanna&#x27;s voice goes quieter.]</p>
<p>Avyanna: The logs. The ration schedule. The number of collapsed people per shift. The way they stamped &quot;noncompliant&quot; on anyone who asked for painkillers.</p>
<p>Vesper: Inference.</p>
<p>Avyanna: The neglect was policy. Not failure.</p>
<p>Vesper: Confounders.</p>
<p>[Avyanna freezes.]</p>
<p>Vesper: This is where you stop being a victim of your own certainty.</p>
<p>Avyanna: [working] Confounders... shortages. Staffing. Flicker day malfunctions.</p>
<p>Vesper: Good.</p>
<p>Vesper: What would prove you wrong.</p>
<p>Avyanna: A supply manifest showing adequate medicine. A record of workers treated promptly.</p>
<p>Vesper: And if those exist.</p>
<p>Avyanna: Then I&#x27;m wrong.</p>
<p>[The words taste strange in her mouth.]</p>
<p>(Wrong means you die.)</p>
<p>[Here, wrong means: adjust.]</p>
<p>Vesper: If you can be proven wrong, you can be trusted.</p>
<p>Avyanna: That&#x27;s... backwards.</p>
<p>Vesper: It&#x27;s adversarial.</p>
<p>Vesper: The people who can&#x27;t be wrong are trying to sell you something.</p>
<hr>
<p>[A pause.]</p>
<p>[Avyanna stares at the blank space on her template labeled WITNESS STATEMENT and feels something in her chest shift.]</p>
<p>Avyanna: This is... how you fight.</p>
<p>Vesper: This is one way.</p>
<p>Vesper: Another way is Elia.</p>
<p>Avyanna: [a small, real laugh] Yes.</p>
<p>[Vesper stands, goes to the shelf, and takes down a thin folder.]</p>
<p>Vesper: Tomorrow we go to arbitration.</p>
<p>Vesper: Today we build the spine.</p>
<p>[She sets the folder in front of Avyanna.]</p>
<p>Vesper: No heroics.</p>
<p>Avyanna: [soft] Just receipts.</p>
<p>Vesper: Just receipts.</p>
<p>[Avyanna opens the folder.]</p>
<p>[This time, the paper doesn&#x27;t feel like a trap.]</p>
<p>[It feels like a handle.]</p>
<hr>
<p>[Vesper doesn&#x27;t let the moment turn sentimental.]</p>
<p>[She flips to a new section in the binder and slides it across.]</p>
<p>&gt; **CROSS-EXAMINATION PREP** &gt; &gt; *If they say you&#x27;re lying, what do you point to?* &gt; &gt; *If they say you misremembered, what do you point to?* &gt; &gt; *If they say it&#x27;s &quot;standard,&quot; what do you ask?*</p>
<p>Avyanna: [reading] What do you ask.</p>
<p>Vesper: &quot;Under which jurisdiction. Enforced by whom. Consequence for refusal.&quot;</p>
<p>Avyanna: [quiet] That&#x27;s... the spine.</p>
<p>Vesper: Yes.</p>
<p>Vesper: When someone is trying to drown you in language, you don&#x27;t swim.</p>
<p>Vesper: You stand on three questions.</p>
<p>[Avyanna&#x27;s pen hovers.]</p>
<p>Avyanna: In the mine, questions got you noticed.</p>
<p>Vesper: Here, questions keep you alive.</p>
<p>[A beat.]</p>
<p>Vesper: Not just physically.</p>
<p>[Avyanna swallows.]</p>
<p>Avyanna: This feels like fighting without... touching anyone.</p>
<p>Vesper: It is.</p>
<p>Vesper: It&#x27;s slower than Elia. But it leaves bodies intact.</p>
<p>Avyanna: [dry] Sometimes.</p>
<p>[Vesper&#x27;s mouth twitches.]</p>
<p>Vesper: Sometimes.</p>
<hr>
<p>[Vesper pulls a small index card from a box and slides it toward Avyanna.]</p>
<p>&gt; **YOUR JOB IN THE ROOM** &gt; &gt; - say what you saw &gt; - don&#x27;t guess &gt; - if you don&#x27;t know, say you don&#x27;t know &gt; - if you need a minute, ask for it</p>
<p>Avyanna: [soft] I can ask for a minute.</p>
<p>Vesper: Yes.</p>
<p>Vesper: If anyone tries to deny you that, I will make it expensive.</p>
<p>[Avyanna&#x27;s throat tightens.]</p>
<p>(Expensive. Protective. Not ownership.)</p>
<hr>
<p>[Vesper taps the face-down Aurum-coded printout with one knuckle.]</p>
<p>Vesper: This.</p>
<p>Avyanna: [tense] Yes.</p>
<p>Vesper: You did not break when you saw it.</p>
<p>Avyanna: I almost did.</p>
<p>Vesper: &quot;Almost&quot; is data.</p>
<p>Avyanna: That&#x27;s... also you.</p>
<p>Vesper: [without apology] Yes.</p>
<p>[She pauses.]</p>
<p>Vesper: When you&#x27;re in the room tomorrow and something tries to pull you back into the mine-</p>
<p>Avyanna: Like a smell. Like a word.</p>
<p>Vesper: -you do not have to white-knuckle it.</p>
<p>Vesper: You can say: &quot;I need to pause.&quot;</p>
<p>Avyanna: [quiet] And nobody will-</p>
<p>Vesper: No penalty.</p>
<p>[The phrase lands like a seal on paper.]</p>
<hr>
<p>[Avyanna writes it down.]</p>
<p>&gt; **NO PENALTY**</p>
<p>[Not in Cinnamon&#x27;s font. In her own.]</p>
<p>[She looks up at Vesper.]</p>
<p>Avyanna: Thank you.</p>
<p>Vesper: [measured] You&#x27;re welcome.</p>
<p>[Vesper straightens Avyanna&#x27;s collar without asking. Then catches herself.]</p>
<p>Vesper: Go drink water.</p>
<p>Avyanna: [blinking] That&#x27;s an order.</p>
<p>Vesper: It&#x27;s medical advice.</p>
<p>Avyanna: [a small smile] Who enforces it.</p>
<p>Vesper: Nyx.</p>
<p>[Avyanna laughs.]</p>
<p>Vesper: And also me.</p>
<p>[The second part is said so quietly it almost doesn&#x27;t count.]</p>
<p>[Almost.]</p>
<p>[Avyanna gathers the folder and the index card like they&#x27;re equipment.]</p>
<p>[Because they are.]</p>
<p>[She leaves Vesper&#x27;s office with her spine built from paper and the strange sensation of being allowed to carry it.]</p>
</div>

