:: Act1 20d Aleena Pulls Elia From Wreckage
<h1>Optional 20d: Aleena Pulls Elia From Wreckage</h1>
<p class="source-note">Source: 20d_aleena_pulls_elia_from_wreckage.md</p>
<div class="scene-prose">
<p>&gt; **[INTERSTITIAL - OCCURS POST-CH20]** &gt; *Trigger: Avyanna watches Elia move through the ship like it belongs to her* &gt; *Purpose: Aleena as origin of &quot;you coming?&quot; as invitation, not leash*</p>
<hr>
<p>[After &quot;The Receipt,&quot; the ship feels too bright.]</p>
<p>[Not because the lights changed.]</p>
<p>[Because Avyanna&#x27;s brain is doing what it always does when something impossible happens:]</p>
<p>[Replaying it until it becomes survivable.]</p>
<p>[She walks the corridor to bleed off the energy.]</p>
<p>[She finds Elia in the maintenance bay, stripped down to a tank and cargo pants, wiping her blades with a cloth that looks too ordinary to be allowed near relic steel.]</p>
<p>[Elia glances up and clocks Avyanna&#x27;s posture in half a second.]</p>
<p>Elia: You&#x27;re vibrating.</p>
<p>Avyanna: I&#x27;m not.</p>
<p>Elia: You are.</p>
<p>[Elia&#x27;s mouth quirks.]</p>
<p>Elia: Want to break something.</p>
<p>Avyanna: No.</p>
<p>Elia: [delighted] Lies.</p>
<p>[Avyanna surprises herself by almost smiling.]</p>
<hr>
<p>[Elia sets the cloth down.]</p>
<p>Elia: What&#x27;s the spiral.</p>
<p>Avyanna: Vesper said-</p>
<p>[Avyanna stops.]</p>
<p>[She doesn&#x27;t know how to say &quot;family&quot; without choking.]</p>
<p>Elia: [softer, still blunt] Yeah.</p>
<p>Elia: That&#x27;ll do it.</p>
<p>[Avyanna&#x27;s gaze flicks to Elia&#x27;s hands.]</p>
<p>[Scarred. Precise. Calm with weapons.]</p>
<p>Avyanna: How did you get like this.</p>
<p>[Elia blinks.]</p>
<p>Elia: Like what.</p>
<p>Avyanna: Like you&#x27;re... not scared.</p>
<p>[Elia laughs once, sharp.]</p>
<p>Elia: I&#x27;m terrified.</p>
<p>Elia: I just don&#x27;t let it drive.</p>
<p>[A beat.]</p>
<p>Elia: Aleena taught me that.</p>
<p>[The name lands with weight. Avyanna has heard it in scraps, in the way Elisira and Elia say it like a rule.]</p>
<p>Avyanna: Who was she.</p>
<p>[Elia&#x27;s eyes go distant.]</p>
<hr>
<p>## Intercut - Wreckage (Aleena Finds a Child)</p>
<p>[Smoke.]</p>
<p>[Hot metal.]</p>
<p>[The kind of silence that comes after alarms die and before the survivors start screaming.]</p>
<p>[Elia is a small bundle in the wreckage.]</p>
<p>[Too young to understand what happened, only old enough to understand that everything hurts and no one is answering.]</p>
<p>[A shadow falls over her.]</p>
<p>[Not a supervisor shadow.]</p>
<p>[A different kind: broad-shouldered, steady, moving through debris like it&#x27;s familiar.]</p>
<p>[Aleena Lagrange kneels.]</p>
<p>[Her face is smeared with soot. There is blood on her sleeve that isn&#x27;t hers. Her eyes are bright with anger that doesn&#x27;t spill onto the child.]</p>
<p>[Aleena doesn&#x27;t reach in and grab.]</p>
<p>[She clears a piece of twisted plating first.]</p>
<p>[Makes space.]</p>
<p>[Then she holds out her hand.]</p>
<p>Aleena: Hey.</p>
<p>[Elia makes a sound that could be a sob, could be a laugh.]</p>
<p>Aleena: You hurt.</p>
<p>Aleena: That&#x27;s real.</p>
<p>Aleena: But you&#x27;re alive.</p>
<p>[Elia stares at the offered hand like it&#x27;s a myth.]</p>
<p>Aleena: You can stay.</p>
<p>Aleena: Or you can come with me.</p>
<p>[A pause.]</p>
<p>Aleena: No penalty.</p>
<p>[Elia doesn&#x27;t know what &quot;penalty&quot; means.]</p>
<p>[She knows what &quot;come with me&quot; means.]</p>
<p>[It means there is a direction.]</p>
<p>[A floor.]</p>
<p>[Elia reaches out with shaking fingers.]</p>
<p>[Aleena closes her hand around Elia&#x27;s wrist, not tight, not taking, just... confirming contact.]</p>
<p>Aleena: You coming?</p>
<p>[Elia doesn&#x27;t have words.]</p>
<p>[Elia nods.]</p>
<hr>
<p>## Return - Maintenance Bay</p>
<p>[Elia&#x27;s gaze snaps back to Avyanna like she realized she left the room for too long.]</p>
<p>Elia: She found me in wreckage.</p>
<p>Elia: Asked.</p>
<p>Elia: Didn&#x27;t take.</p>
<p>[Avyanna&#x27;s throat tightens.]</p>
<p>Avyanna: She said &quot;you coming?&quot;</p>
<p>Elia: [a small nod] Yeah.</p>
<p>Elia: That&#x27;s the whole thing.</p>
<p>Elia: It&#x27;s not a command.</p>
<p>Elia: It&#x27;s a door.</p>
<p>[Elia picks up the cloth again, wipes a blade edge with ritual care.]</p>
<p>Elia: Sometimes you hold the door.</p>
<p>Elia: Sometimes you walk through it.</p>
<p>Elia: Sometimes you kick it down.</p>
<p>[She looks up, eyes bright with something that might be grief and might be joy.]</p>
<p>Elia: But it&#x27;s always your feet.</p>
<p>[Avyanna swallows.]</p>
<p>Avyanna: Okay.</p>
<p>Elia: [crooked] Good.</p>
<p>Elia: Now go do whatever your vibrating problem is.</p>
<p>Avyanna: [deadpan] That was emotional.</p>
<p>Elia: [immediately defensive] It was practical.</p>
<p>[Avyanna walks out of the bay with her chest tight and her spine a fraction straighter.]</p>
<p>[A door, offered.]</p>
<p>[A phrase that means: choose.]</p>
<hr>
<p>*End Chapter 20d*</p>
</div>

